62 CConfig::CConfig(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE], SU2_COMPONENT val_software, bool verb_high) {
63 
64  /*--- Set the case name to the base config file name without extension ---*/
65 
66  caseName = PrintingToolbox::split(string(case_filename),'.')[0];
67 
68  base_config = true;
69 
70  /*--- Store MPI rank and size ---*/
71 
72  rank = SU2_MPI::GetRank();
73  size = SU2_MPI::GetSize();
74 
75  iZone = 0;
76  nZone = 1;
77 
78  Init();
79 
80  /*--- Parsing the config file ---*/
81 
82  SetConfig_Parsing(case_filename);
83 
84  /*--- Set the default values for all of the options that weren't set ---*/
85 
86  SetDefault();
87 
88  /*--- Set number of zone ---*/
89 
90  SetnZone();
91 
92  /*--- Configuration file postprocessing ---*/
93 
94  SetPostprocessing(val_software, iZone, 0);
95 
96  /*--- Configuration file boundaries/markers setting ---*/
97 
98  SetMarkers(val_software);
99 
100  /*--- Configuration file output ---*/
101 
102  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && verb_high)
103  SetOutput(val_software, iZone);
104 
105 }
106 
107 CConfig::CConfig(istream &case_buffer, SU2_COMPONENT val_software, bool verb_high) {
108 
109  base_config = true;
110 
111  iZone = 0;
112  nZone = 1;
113 
114  Init();
115 
116  /*--- Parsing the config file ---*/
117 
118  SetConfig_Parsing(case_buffer);
119 
120  /*--- Set the default values for all of the options that weren't set ---*/
121 
122  SetDefault();
123 
124  /*--- Set number of zone ---*/
125 
126  SetnZone();
127 
128  /*--- Configuration file postprocessing ---*/
129 
130  SetPostprocessing(val_software, iZone, 0);
131 
132  /*--- Configuration file boundaries/markers setting ---*/
133 
134  SetMarkers(val_software);
135 
136  /*--- Configuration file output ---*/
137 
138  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && verb_high)
139  SetOutput(val_software, iZone);
140 
141 }

143 CConfig::CConfig(CConfig* config, char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE], SU2_COMPONENT val_software, unsigned short val_iZone, unsigned short val_nZone, bool verb_high) {
144 
145  caseName = config->GetCaseName();
146 
147  unsigned short val_nDim;
148 
149  base_config = false;
150 
151  iZone = val_iZone;
152  nZone = val_nZone;
153 
154  Init();
155 
156  /*--- Parsing the config file ---*/
157 
158  SetConfig_Parsing(case_filename);
159 
160  /*--- Set default options from base config ---*/
161 
162  SetDefaultFromConfig(config);
163 
164  /*--- Set the default values for all of the options that weren't set ---*/
165 
166  SetDefault();
167 
168  /*--- Get the dimension --- */
169 
170  val_nDim = GetnDim(Mesh_FileName, Mesh_FileFormat);
171 
172  /*--- Configuration file postprocessing ---*/
173 
174  SetPostprocessing(val_software, val_iZone, val_nDim);
175 
176  /*--- Configuration file boundaries/markers setting ---*/
177 
178  SetMarkers(val_software);
179 
180  /*--- Configuration file output ---*/
181 
182  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && verb_high)
183  SetOutput(val_software, val_iZone);
184 
185  Multizone_Problem = config->GetMultizone_Problem();
186 
187 }
188 
189 CConfig::CConfig(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE], SU2_COMPONENT val_software) {
190 
191  /*--- Set the case name to the base config file name without extension ---*/
192 
193  caseName = PrintingToolbox::split(string(case_filename),'.')[0];
194 
195  base_config = true;
196 
197  nZone = 1;
198  iZone = 0;
199 
200  Init();
201 
202  /*--- Parsing the config file ---*/
203 
204  SetConfig_Parsing(case_filename);
205 
206  /*--- Set the default values for all of the options that weren't set ---*/
207 
208  SetDefault();
209 
210  /*--- Set number of zones --- */
211 
212  SetnZone();
213 
214  /*--- Configuration file postprocessing ---*/
215 
216  SetPostprocessing(val_software, 0, 1);
217 
218  /*--- Configuration file boundaries/markers setting ---*/
219 
220  SetMarkers(val_software);
221 
222  /*--- Print the header --- */
223 
224  SetHeader(val_software);
225 
226 }
227 
228 CConfig::CConfig(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE], CConfig *config) {
229 
230  /*--- Set the case name to the base config file name without extension ---*/
231 
232  caseName = PrintingToolbox::split(string(case_filename),'.')[0];
233 
234  base_config = true;
235 
236  bool runtime_file = false;
237 
238  Init();
239 
240  /*--- Parsing the config file ---*/
241 
242  runtime_file = SetRunTime_Parsing(case_filename);
243 
244  /*--- Set the default values for all of the options that weren't set ---*/
245 
246  SetDefault();
247 
248  /*--- Update original config file ---*/
249 
250  if (runtime_file) {
251  if (all_options.find("TIME_ITER") == all_options.end())
252  config->SetnTime_Iter(nTimeIter);
253  }
254 }

260 }

262 void CConfig::Init(){
263 
264  /*--- Store MPI rank and size ---*/
265 
266  rank = SU2_MPI::GetRank();
267  size = SU2_MPI::GetSize();
268 
269  /*--- Initialize pointers to Null---*/
270 
271  SetPointersNull();
272 
273  /*--- Reading config options ---*/
274 
275  SetConfig_Options();
276 
277 }
278 
279 void CConfig::SetMPICommunicator(SU2_MPI::Comm Communicator) {
280 
281  SU2_Communicator = Communicator;
282 
283 }
284 
285 void CConfig::addDoubleOption(const string name, su2double & option_field, su2double default_value) {
286  // Check if the key is already in the map. If this fails, it is coder error
287  // and not user error, so throw.
288  assert(option_map.find(name) == option_map.end());
289 
290  // Add this option to the list of all the options
291  all_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(name, true));
292 
293  // Create the parser for a su2double option with a reference to the option_field and the desired
294  // default value. This will take the string in the config file, convert it to a su2double, and
295  // place that su2double in the memory location specified by the reference.
296  COptionBase* val = new COptionDouble(name, option_field, default_value);
297 
298  // Create an association between the option name ("CFL") and the parser generated above.
299  // During configuration, the parsing script will get the option name, and use this map
300  // to find how to parse that option.
301  option_map.insert(pair<string, COptionBase *>(name, val));
302 }
303 
304 void CConfig::addStringOption(const string name, string & option_field, string default_value) {
305 
306  assert(option_map.find(name) == option_map.end());
307  all_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(name, true));
308  COptionBase* val = new COptionString(name, option_field, default_value);
309  option_map.insert(pair<string, COptionBase *>(name, val));
310 }

347 // enum types work differently than all of the others because there are a small number of valid
348 // string entries for the type. One must also provide a list of all the valid strings of that type.
349 template <class Tenum, class TField>
350 void CConfig::addEnumOption(const string name, TField& option_field, const map<string,Tenum>& enum_map, Tenum default_value) {
351  assert(option_map.find(name) == option_map.end());
352  all_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(name, true));
353  COptionBase* val = new COptionEnum<Tenum, TField>(name, enum_map, option_field, default_value);
354  option_map.insert(pair<string, COptionBase *>(name, val));
355  return;
356 }
357 
358 // input_size is the number of options read in from the config file
359 template <class Tenum, class TField>
360 void CConfig::addEnumListOption(const string name, unsigned short& input_size, TField*& option_field, const map<string, Tenum>& enum_map) {
361  input_size = 0;
362  assert(option_map.find(name) == option_map.end());
363  all_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(name, true));
364  COptionBase* val = new COptionEnumList<Tenum,TField>(name, enum_map, option_field, input_size);
365  option_map.insert( pair<string, COptionBase*>(name, val) );
366 }

551  su2double** & ActDisk_TempJump, su2double** & ActDisk_Omega) {
552  assert(option_map.find(name) == option_map.end());
553  all_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(name, true));
554  COptionBase* val = new COptionActDisk(name, nMarker_ActDiskInlet, nMarker_ActDiskOutlet, Marker_ActDiskInlet,
555  Marker_ActDiskOutlet, ActDisk_PressJump, ActDisk_TempJump, ActDisk_Omega);
556  option_map.insert(pair<string, COptionBase *>(name, val));
557 }

575 
576 unsigned short CConfig::GetnZone(string val_mesh_filename, unsigned short val_format) {
577 
578  int nZone = 1; /* Default value if nothing is specified. */
579 
580  switch (val_format) {
581  case SU2: {
582 
583  /*--- Local variables for reading the SU2 file. ---*/
584  string text_line;
585  ifstream mesh_file;
586 
587  /*--- Check if the mesh file can be opened for reading. ---*/
588  mesh_file.open(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), ios::in);
589  if (mesh_file.fail())
590  SU2_MPI::Error(string("There is no geometry file called ") + val_mesh_filename,
591  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
592 
593  /*--- Read the SU2 mesh file until the zone data is reached or
594  when it can be decided that it is not present. ---*/
595  while( getline (mesh_file, text_line) ) {
596 
597  /*--- Search for the "NZONE" keyword to see if there are multiple Zones ---*/
598  if(text_line.find ("NZONE=",0) != string::npos) {
599  text_line.erase (0,6); nZone = atoi(text_line.c_str());
600  break;
601  }
602 
603  /*--- If one of the keywords IZONE, NELEM or NPOIN, NMARK is encountered,
604  it can be assumed that the NZONE keyword is not present and the loop
605  can be terminated. ---*/
606  if(text_line.find ("IZONE=",0) != string::npos) break;
607  if(text_line.find ("NELEM=",0) != string::npos) break;
608  if(text_line.find ("NPOIN=",0) != string::npos) break;
609  if(text_line.find ("NMARK=",0) != string::npos) break;
610  }
611 
612  mesh_file.close();
613  break;
614 
615  }
616 
617  case CGNS_GRID: {
618 
619 #ifdef HAVE_CGNS
620 
621  /*--- Local variables which are needed when calling the CGNS mid-level API. ---*/
622 
623  int fn, nbases = 0, nzones = 0, file_type;
624  int cell_dim = 0, phys_dim = 0;
625  char basename[CGNS_STRING_SIZE];
626 
627  /*--- Check whether the supplied file is truly a CGNS file. ---*/
628 
629  if ( cg_is_cgns(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), &file_type) != CG_OK ) {
630  SU2_MPI::Error(val_mesh_filename +
631  string(" was not found or is not a properly formatted CGNS file.\n") +
632  string("Note that SU2 expects unstructured CGNS files in ADF data format."),
633  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
634  }
635 
636  /*--- Open the CGNS file for reading. The value of fn returned
637  is the specific index number for this file and will be
638  repeatedly used in the function calls. ---*/
639 
640  if (cg_open(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), CG_MODE_READ, &fn)) cg_error_exit();
641 
642  /*--- Get the number of databases. This is the highest node
643  in the CGNS heirarchy. ---*/
644 
645  if (cg_nbases(fn, &nbases)) cg_error_exit();
646 
647  /*--- Check if there is more than one database. Throw an
648  error if there is because this reader can currently
649  only handle one database. ---*/
650 
651  if ( nbases > 1 ) {
652  SU2_MPI::Error("CGNS reader currently incapable of handling more than 1 database." ,
653  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
654  }
655 
656  /*--- Read the databases. Note that the indexing starts at 1. ---*/
657 
658  for ( int i = 1; i <= nbases; i++ ) {
659 
660  if (cg_base_read(fn, i, basename, &cell_dim, &phys_dim)) cg_error_exit();
661 
662  /*--- Get the number of zones for this base. ---*/
663 
664  if (cg_nzones(fn, i, &nzones)) cg_error_exit();
665 
666  }
667 
668  /*--- Close the CGNS file. ---*/
669 
670  if ( cg_close(fn) ) cg_error_exit();
671 
672  /*--- Set the number of zones as read from the CGNS file ---*/
673 
674  nZone = nzones;
675 
676 #else
677  SU2_MPI::Error(string(" SU2 built without CGNS support. \n") +
678  string(" To use CGNS, build SU2 accordingly."),
679  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
680 #endif
681 
682  break;
683  }
684  case RECTANGLE: {
685  nZone = 1;
686  break;
687  }
688  case BOX: {
689  nZone = 1;
690  break;
691  }
692  }
693 
694  return (unsigned short) nZone;
695 
696 }
697 
698 unsigned short CConfig::GetnDim(string val_mesh_filename, unsigned short val_format) {
699 
700  short nDim = -1;
701 
702  switch (val_format) {
703  case SU2: {
704 
705  /*--- Local variables for reading the SU2 file. ---*/
706  string text_line;
707  ifstream mesh_file;
708 
709  /*--- Open grid file ---*/
710  mesh_file.open(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), ios::in);
711  if (mesh_file.fail()) {
712  SU2_MPI::Error(string("The SU2 mesh file named ") + val_mesh_filename + string(" was not found."), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
713  }
714 
715  /*--- Read the SU2 mesh file until the dimension data is reached
716  or when it can be decided that it is not present. ---*/
717  while( getline (mesh_file, text_line) ) {
718 
719  /*--- Search for the "NDIME" keyword to determine the number
720  of dimensions. ---*/
721  if(text_line.find ("NDIME=",0) != string::npos) {
722  text_line.erase (0,6); nDim = atoi(text_line.c_str());
723  break;
724  }
725 
726  /*--- If one of the keywords NELEM or NPOIN, NMARK is encountered,
727  it can be assumed that the NZONE keyword is not present and
728  the loop can be terminated. ---*/
729  if(text_line.find ("NELEM=",0) != string::npos) break;
730  if(text_line.find ("NPOIN=",0) != string::npos) break;
731  if(text_line.find ("NMARK=",0) != string::npos) break;
732  }
733 
734  mesh_file.close();
735 
736  /*--- Throw an error if the dimension was not found. ---*/
737  if (nDim == -1) {
738  SU2_MPI::Error(val_mesh_filename + string(" is not an SU2 mesh file or has the wrong format \n ('NDIME=' not found). Please check."),
739  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
740  }
741 
742  break;
743  }
744 
745  case CGNS_GRID: {
746 
747 #ifdef HAVE_CGNS
748 
749  /*--- Local variables which are needed when calling the CGNS mid-level API. ---*/
750  int fn, nbases, file_type;
751  int cell_dim, phys_dim;
752  char basename[CGNS_STRING_SIZE];
753 
754  /*--- Check whether the supplied file is truly a CGNS file. ---*/
755  if ( cg_is_cgns(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), &file_type) != CG_OK ) {
756  SU2_MPI::Error(val_mesh_filename +
757  string(" was not found or is not a properly formatted CGNS file.\n") +
758  string("Note that SU2 expects unstructured CGNS files in ADF data format."),
759  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
760  }
761 
762  /*--- Open the CGNS file for reading. The value of fn returned
763  is the specific index number for this file and will be
764  repeatedly used in the function calls. ---*/
765  if (cg_open(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), CG_MODE_READ, &fn) != CG_OK) cg_error_exit();
766 
767  /*--- Get the number of databases. This is the highest node
768  in the CGNS heirarchy. ---*/
769  if (cg_nbases(fn, &nbases) != CG_OK) cg_error_exit();
770 
771  /*--- Check if there is more than one database. Throw an
772  error if there is because this reader can currently
773  only handle one database. ---*/
774  if ( nbases > 1 )
775  SU2_MPI::Error("CGNS reader currently incapable of handling more than 1 database." ,
776  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
777 
778  /*--- Read the database. Note that the indexing starts at 1.
779  Afterwards close the file again. ---*/
780  if (cg_base_read(fn, 1, basename, &cell_dim, &phys_dim) != CG_OK) cg_error_exit();
781  if (cg_close(fn) != CG_OK) cg_error_exit();
782 
783  /*--- Set the problem dimension as read from the CGNS file ---*/
784  nDim = cell_dim;
785 
786 #else
787  SU2_MPI::Error(string(" SU2 built without CGNS support. \n") +
788  string(" To use CGNS, build SU2 accordingly."),
789  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
790 #endif
791 
792  break;
793  }
794  case RECTANGLE: {
795  nDim = 2;
796  break;
797  }
798  case BOX: {
799  nDim = 3;
800  break;
801  }
802  }
803 
804  /*--- After reading the mesh, assert that the dimension is equal to 2 or 3. ---*/
805  assert((nDim == 2) || (nDim == 3));
806 
807  return (unsigned short) nDim;
808 }

1070 
1071 void CConfig::SetConfig_Options() {
1072 
1073  // This config file is parsed by a number of programs to make it easy to write SU2
1074  // wrapper scripts (in python, go, etc.) so please do
1075  // the best you can to follow the established format. It's very hard to parse c++ code
1076  // and none of us that write the parsers want to write a full c++ interpreter. Please
1077  // play nice with the existing format so that you don't break the existing scripts.
1078 
1079  /* BEGIN_CONFIG_OPTIONS */
1080 
1081  /*!\par CONFIG_CATEGORY: Problem Definition \ingroup Config */
1082  /*--- Options related to problem definition and partitioning ---*/
1083 
1084  /*!\brief SOLVER \n DESCRIPTION: Type of solver \n Options: see \link Solver_Map \endlink \n DEFAULT: NONE \ingroup Config*/
1085  addEnumOption("SOLVER", Kind_Solver, Solver_Map, MAIN_SOLVER::NONE);
1086  /*!\brief MULTIZONE \n DESCRIPTION: Enable multizone mode \ingroup Config*/
1087  addBoolOption("MULTIZONE", Multizone_Problem, NO);
1088  /*!\brief PHYSICAL_PROBLEM \n DESCRIPTION: Physical governing equations \n Options: see \link Solver_Map \endlink \n DEFAULT: NONE \ingroup Config*/
1089  addEnumOption("MULTIZONE_SOLVER", Kind_MZSolver, Multizone_Map, ENUM_MULTIZONE::MZ_BLOCK_GAUSS_SEIDEL);
1090 #ifdef CODI_REVERSE_TYPE
1091  const bool discAdjDefault = true;
1092 #else
1093  const bool discAdjDefault = false;
1094 #endif
1095  /*!\brief MATH_PROBLEM \n DESCRIPTION: Mathematical problem \n Options: DIRECT, ADJOINT \ingroup Config*/
1096  addMathProblemOption("MATH_PROBLEM", ContinuousAdjoint, false, DiscreteAdjoint, discAdjDefault, Restart_Flow, discAdjDefault);
1097  /*!\brief KIND_TURB_MODEL \n DESCRIPTION: Specify turbulence model \n Options: see \link Turb_Model_Map \endlink \n DEFAULT: NONE \ingroup Config*/

2271  - ROTATION ( x_Orig, y_Orig, z_Orig, x_End, y_End, z_End )
2272  - OBSTACLE ( Center, Bump size )
2273  - SPHERICAL ( ControlPoint_Index, Theta_Disp, R_Disp )

2927 void CConfig::SetConfig_Parsing(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE]) {
2928 
2929  ifstream case_file;
2930 
2931  /*--- Read the configuration file ---*/
2932 
2933  case_file.open(case_filename, ios::in);
2934 
2935  if (case_file.fail()) {
2936  SU2_MPI::Error("The configuration file (.cfg) is missing!!", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2937  }
2938 
2939  SetConfig_Parsing(case_file);
2940 
2941  case_file.close();
2942 
2943 }
2944 
2945 void CConfig::SetConfig_Parsing(istream& config_buffer){
2946 
2947  string text_line, option_name;
2948  vector<string> option_value;
2949 
2950  string errorString;
2951 
2952  const int max_err_count = 30; // Maximum number of errors to print before stopping
2953  int err_count = 0; // How many errors have we found in the config file
2954  int line_count = 1;
2955 
2956  map<string, bool> included_options;
2957 
2958  /*--- Parse the configuration file and set the options ---*/
2959 
2960  while (getline (config_buffer, text_line)) {
2961 
2962  if (err_count >= max_err_count) {
2963  errorString.append("Too many errors, stopping parse.");
2964  break;
2965  }
2966 
2967  PrintingToolbox::trim(text_line);
2968 
2969  /*--- Check if there is a line continuation character at the
2970  * end of the current line or somewhere in between (the rest is ignored then).
2971  * If yes, read until there is a line without one or an empty line.
2972  * If there is a statement after a cont. char
2973  * throw an error. ---*/
2974 
2975  if (text_line.size() && (text_line.front() != '%')){
2976  while (text_line.back() == '\\' ||
2977  (PrintingToolbox::split(text_line, '\\').size() > 1)){
2978  string tmp;
2979  getline (config_buffer, tmp);
2980  line_count++;
2981  if (tmp.find_first_of('=') != string::npos){
2982  errorString.append("Line " + to_string(line_count) + ": Statement found after continuation character.\n");
2983  }
2984  PrintingToolbox::trim(tmp);
2985  if (tmp.front() != '%'){
2986  text_line = PrintingToolbox::split(text_line, '\\')[0];
2987  text_line += " " + tmp;
2988  }
2989  }
2990  }
2991 
2992  if (TokenizeString(text_line, option_name, option_value)) {
2993  /*--- See if it's a python option ---*/
2994 
2995  if (option_map.find(option_name) == option_map.end()) {
2996  string newString;
2997  newString.append("Line " + to_string(line_count) + " " + option_name);
2998  newString.append(": invalid option name");
2999  newString.append(". Check current SU2 options in config_template.cfg.");
3000  newString.append("\n");
3001  if (!option_name.compare("RELAXATION_FACTOR_ADJFLOW"))
3002  newString.append("Option RELAXATION_FACTOR_ADJFLOW is now RELAXATION_FACTOR_ADJOINT, "
3003  "and it also applies to discrete adjoint problems.\n\n");
3004  else if (!option_name.compare("WRT_MESH_QUALITY"))
3005  newString.append("WRT_MESH_QUALITY is deprecated. Use VOLUME_OUTPUT= (MESH_QUALITY, ...) instead.\n\n");
3006  else if (!option_name.compare("VISUALIZE_SURFACE_DEF"))
3007  newString.append("VISUALIZE_SURFACE_DEF is deprecated. Simply add a surface format to OUTPUT_FILES.\n\n");
3008  else if (!option_name.compare("VISUALIZE_VOLUME_DEF"))
3009  newString.append("VISUALIZE_VOLUME_DEF is deprecated. Simply add a volume format to OUTPUT_FILES.\n\n");
3010  else if (!option_name.compare("WRT_BINARY_RESTART"))
3011  newString.append("WRT_BINARY_RESTART is deprecated. The type of restart is determined from the OUTPUT_FILES list.\n\n");
3012  else if (!option_name.compare("WRT_RESIDUALS"))
3013  newString.append("WRT_RESIDUALS is deprecated. Use VOLUME_OUTPUT= ( RESIDUAL, ... ) instead.\n\n");
3014  else if (!option_name.compare("WRT_LIMITERS"))
3015  newString.append("WRT_LIMITERS is deprecated. Use VOLUME_OUTPUT= ( LIMITER, ... ) instead.\n\n");
3016  else if (!option_name.compare("WRT_CON_FREQ"))
3017  newString.append("WRT_CON_FREQ is deprecated. Use SCREEN_WRT_FREQ_INNER or SCREEN_WRT_FREQ_OUTER for multizone cases instead.\n\n");
3018  else if (!option_name.compare("WRT_CON_FREQ_DUALTIME"))
3019  newString.append("WRT_CON_FREQ_DUALTIME is deprecated. Use SCREEN_WRT_FREQ_TIME instead.\n\n");
3020  else if (!option_name.compare("WRT_SRF_SOL"))
3021  newString.append("WRT_SRF_SOL is deprecated. Simply add a surface format to OUTPUT_FILES.\n\n");
3022  else if (!option_name.compare("WRT_CSV_SOL"))
3023  newString.append("WRT_CSV_SOL is deprecated. Simply add a CSV format to OUTPUT_FILES.\n\n");
3024  else if (!option_name.compare("WRT_SOL_FREQ"))
3025  newString.append("WRT_SOL_FREQ is deprecated. Use OUTPUT_WRT_FREQ instead.\n\n");
3026  else if (!option_name.compare("WRT_SOL_FREQ_DUALTIME"))
3027  newString.append("WRT_SOL_FREQ_DUALTIME is deprecated. Use OUTPUT_WRT_FREQ instead.\n\n");
3028  else if (!option_name.compare("UNST_RESTART_ITER"))
3029  newString.append("UNST_RESTART_ITER is deprecated. Use RESTART_ITER instead.\n\n");
3030  else if (!option_name.compare("DYN_RESTART_ITER"))
3031  newString.append("DYN_RESTART_ITER is deprecated. Use RESTART_ITER instead.\n\n");
3032  else if (!option_name.compare("CONV_CRITERIA"))
3033  newString.append("CONV_CRITERIA is deprecated. SU2 will choose the criteria automatically based on the CONV_FIELD.\n"
3034  "RESIDUAL for any RMS_* BGS_* value. CAUCHY for coefficients like DRAG etc.\n\n");
3035  else if (!option_name.compare("THERMAL_DIFFUSIVITY"))
3036  newString.append("THERMAL_DIFFUSIVITY is deprecated. See the INC_ENERGY_EQUATION options instead.\n\n");
3037  else if (!option_name.compare("THERMAL_DIFFUSIVITY_SOLID"))
3038  newString.append("THERMAL_DIFFUSIVITY_SOLID is deprecated. Set THERMAL_CONDUCTIVITY_CONSTANT, MATERIAL_DENSITY and SPECIFIC_HEAT_CP instead.\n\n");
3039  else if (!option_name.compare("SOLID_THERMAL_CONDUCTIVITY"))
3040  newString.append("SOLID_THERMAL_CONDUCTIVITY is deprecated. Use THERMAL_CONDUCTIVITY_CONSTANT instead.\n\n");
3041  else if (!option_name.compare("SOLID_DENSITY"))
3042  newString.append("SOLID_DENSITY is deprecated. Use MATERIAL_DENSITY instead.\n\n");
3043  else if (!option_name.compare("SOLID_TEMPERATURE_INIT"))
3044  newString.append("SOLID_TEMPERATURE_INIT is deprecated. Use FREESTREAM_TEMPERATURE instead.\n\n");
3045  else if (!option_name.compare("SA_QCR"))
3046  newString.append("SA_QCR is deprecated. Use SA_OPTIONS=QCR2000 instead.\n\n");
3047  else {
3048  /*--- Find the most likely candidate for the unrecognized option, based on the length
3049  of start and end character sequences shared by candidates and the option. ---*/
3050  auto countMatchChars = [&option_name](const string& candidate) {
3051  const size_t sz1 = option_name.size(), sz2 = candidate.size();
3052  size_t nMatch = 0;
3053  for (size_t i=0; i<min(sz1,sz2); ++i) {
3054  if (option_name[i] == candidate[i]) nMatch++;
3055  else break;
3056  }
3057  for (size_t i=0; i<min(sz1,sz2); ++i) {
3058  if (option_name[sz1-1-i] == candidate[sz2-1-i]) nMatch++;
3059  else break;
3060  }
3061  return nMatch;
3062  };
3063  string match;
3064  size_t maxScore = 0;
3065  for (auto& candidate : option_map) {
3066  auto score = countMatchChars(candidate.first);
3067  if (score > maxScore) {
3068  maxScore = score;
3069  match = candidate.first;
3070  }
3071  }
3072  newString.append("Did you mean ");
3073  newString.append(match);
3074  newString.append("?\n");
3075  }
3076  errorString.append(newString);
3077  err_count++;
3078  line_count++;
3079  continue;
3080  }
3081 
3082  /*--- Option exists, check if the option has already been in the config file ---*/
3083 
3084  if (included_options.find(option_name) != included_options.end()) {
3085  string newString;
3086  newString.append("Line " + to_string(line_count) + " " + option_name);
3087  newString.append(": option appears twice");
3088  newString.append("\n");
3089  errorString.append(newString);
3090  err_count++;
3091  line_count++;
3092  continue;
3093  }
3094 
3095  /*--- New found option. Add it to the map, and delete from all options ---*/
3096 
3097  included_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(option_name, true));
3098  all_options.erase(option_name);
3099 
3100  /*--- Set the value and check error ---*/
3101 
3102  string out = option_map[option_name]->SetValue(option_value);
3103  if (out.compare("") != 0) {
3104  /*--- valid option, but deprecated value ---*/
3105  if (!option_name.compare("KIND_TURB_MODEL")) {
3106  if (option_value[0] == "SST_SUST")
3107  errorString.append("Option KIND_TURB_MODEL=SST_SUST is deprecated. Use KIND_TURB_MODEL=SST, SST_OPTIONS=SUSTAINING instead.\n");
3108  else if (option_value[0] == "SA_NEG")
3109  errorString.append("Option KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA_NEG is deprecated. Use KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA, SA_OPTIONS=NEGATIVE instead.\n");
3110  else if (option_value[0] == "SA_E")
3111  errorString.append("Option KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA_E is deprecated. Use KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA, SA_OPTIONS=EDWARDS instead.\n");
3112  else if (option_value[0] == "SA_COMP")
3113  errorString.append("Option KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA_COMP is deprecated. Use KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA, SA_OPTIONS=COMPRESSIBILITY instead.\n");
3114  else if (option_value[0] == "SA_E_COMP")
3115  errorString.append("Option KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA_E_COMP is deprecated. Use KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA, SA_OPTIONS=EDWARDS,COMPRESSIBILITY instead.\n");
3116  } else if (!option_name.compare("KIND_TRANS_MODEL")) {
3117  if (option_value[0] == "BC")
3118  errorString.append("Option KIND_TRANS_MODEL=BC is deprecated. Use KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA, SA_OPTIONS=BCM instead.\n");
3119  }
3120  errorString.append(out);
3121  errorString.append("\n");
3122  err_count++;
3123  }
3124  }
3125  line_count++;
3126  }
3127 
3128  /*--- See if there were any errors parsing the config file ---*/
3129 
3130  if (errorString.size() != 0) {
3131  SU2_MPI::Error(errorString, CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3132  }
3133 }

3135 void CConfig::SetDefaultFromConfig(CConfig *config){
3136 
3137  map<string, bool> noInheritance = {{"SCREEN_OUTPUT", true},{"HISTORY_OUTPUT", true}};
3138 
3139  map<string, bool>::iterator iter = all_options.begin(), curr_iter;
3140 
3141  while (iter != all_options.end()){
3142  curr_iter = iter++;
3143  if (config->option_map[curr_iter->first]->GetValue().size() > 0 && !noInheritance[curr_iter->first]){
3144  option_map[curr_iter->first]->SetValue(config->option_map[curr_iter->first]->GetValue());
3145  all_options.erase(curr_iter);
3146  }
3147  }

3150 void CConfig::SetDefault(){

3160 bool CConfig::SetRunTime_Parsing(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE]) {
3161  string text_line, option_name;
3162  ifstream case_file;
3163  vector<string> option_value;
3164 
3165  /*--- Read the configuration file ---*/
3166 
3167  case_file.open(case_filename, ios::in);
3168 
3169  if (case_file.fail()) { return false; }
3170 
3171  string errorString;
3172 
3173  int err_count = 0; // How many errors have we found in the config file
3174  const int max_err_count = 30; // Maximum number of errors to print before stopping
3175 
3176  map<string, bool> included_options;
3177 
3178  /*--- Parse the configuration file and set the options ---*/
3179 
3180  while (getline (case_file, text_line)) {
3181 
3182  if (err_count >= max_err_count) {
3183  errorString.append("Too many errors, stopping parse.");
3184  break;
3185  }
3186 
3187  if (TokenizeString(text_line, option_name, option_value)) {
3188 
3189  if (option_map.find(option_name) == option_map.end()) {
3190 
3191  /*--- See if it's a python option ---*/
3192 
3193  string newString;
3194  newString.append(option_name);
3195  newString.append(": invalid option name");
3196  newString.append("\n");
3197  errorString.append(newString);
3198  err_count++;
3199  continue;
3200  }
3201 
3202  /*--- Option exists, check if the option has already been in the config file ---*/
3203 
3204  if (included_options.find(option_name) != included_options.end()) {
3205  string newString;
3206  newString.append(option_name);
3207  newString.append(": option appears twice");
3208  newString.append("\n");
3209  errorString.append(newString);
3210  err_count++;
3211  continue;
3212  }
3213 
3214  /*--- New found option. Add it to the map, and delete from all options ---*/
3215 
3216  included_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(option_name, true));
3217  all_options.erase(option_name);
3218 
3219  /*--- Set the value and check error ---*/
3220 
3221  string out = option_map[option_name]->SetValue(option_value);
3222  if (out.compare("") != 0) {
3223  errorString.append(out);
3224  errorString.append("\n");
3225  err_count++;
3226  }
3227 
3228  }
3229  }
3230 
3231  /*--- Set the default values for all of the options that weren't set ---*/
3232 
3233  for (map<string, bool>::iterator iter = all_options.begin(); iter != all_options.end(); ++iter) {
3234  option_map[iter->first]->SetDefault();
3235  }
3236 
3237  /*--- See if there were any errors parsing the runtime file ---*/
3238 
3239  if (errorString.size() != 0) {
3240  SU2_MPI::Error(errorString, CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3241  }
3242 
3243  case_file.close();
3244 
3245  return true;
3246 
3247 }

3290 void CConfig::SetnZone(){
3291 
3292  /*--- Just as a clarification --- */
3293 
3294  if (Multizone_Problem == NO && Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::MULTIPHYSICS){
3295  nZone = 1;
3296  }
3297 
3298  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::MULTIPHYSICS){
3299  Multizone_Problem = YES;
3300  if (nConfig_Files == 0){
3301  SU2_MPI::Error("CONFIG_LIST must be provided if PHYSICAL_PROBLEM=MULTIPHYSICS", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3302  }
3303  }
3304 
3305  if (Multizone_Problem == YES){
3306 
3307  /*--- Some basic multizone checks ---*/
3308 
3309  if (nMarker_ZoneInterface % 2 != 0){
3310  SU2_MPI::Error("Number of markers in MARKER_ZONE_INTERFACE must be a multiple of 2", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3311  }
3312 
3313  SinglezoneDriver = NO;
3314 
3315  if (Multizone_Mesh){
3316 
3317  /*--- Get the number of zones from the mesh file --- */
3318 
3319  nZone = GetnZone(Mesh_FileName, Mesh_FileFormat);
3320 
3321  /*--- If config list is set, make sure number matches number of zones in mesh file --- */
3322 
3323  if (nConfig_Files != 0 && (nZone != nConfig_Files)){
3324  SU2_MPI::Error("Number of CONFIG_LIST must match number of zones in mesh file.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3325  }
3326  } else {
3327 
3328  /*--- Number of zones is determined from the number of config files provided --- */
3329 
3330  if (nConfig_Files == 0){
3331  SU2_MPI::Error("If MULTIZONE_MESH is set to YES, you must provide a list of config files using CONFIG_LIST option", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3332  }
3333  nZone = nConfig_Files;
3334 
3335  }
3336 
3337  /*--- Check if subconfig files exist --- */
3338 
3339  if (nConfig_Files != 0){
3340  for (unsigned short iConfig = 0; iConfig < nConfig_Files; iConfig++){
3341  ifstream f(Config_Filenames[iConfig].c_str());
3342  if (!f.good()){
3343  SU2_MPI::Error("Config file " + Config_Filenames[iConfig] + " defined in CONFIG_FILES does not exist", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3344  }
3345  }
3346  }
3347 
3348  }

3352 void CConfig::SetPostprocessing(SU2_COMPONENT val_software, unsigned short val_izone, unsigned short val_nDim) {
3353 
3354  unsigned short iCFL, iMarker;
3355  bool ideal_gas = ((Kind_FluidModel == STANDARD_AIR) ||
3356  (Kind_FluidModel == IDEAL_GAS) ||
3357  (Kind_FluidModel == INC_IDEAL_GAS) ||
3358  (Kind_FluidModel == FLUID_MIXTURE) ||
3359  (Kind_FluidModel == INC_IDEAL_GAS_POLY) ||
3360  (Kind_FluidModel == CONSTANT_DENSITY));
3361  bool noneq_gas = ((Kind_FluidModel == MUTATIONPP) ||
3362  (Kind_FluidModel == SU2_NONEQ));
3363  bool standard_air = ((Kind_FluidModel == STANDARD_AIR));
3364  bool nemo = GetNEMOProblem();
3365 
3366  if (nZone > 1){
3367  Multizone_Problem = YES;
3368  }
3369 
3370  /*--- Set the default output files ---*/
3371  if (!OptionIsSet("OUTPUT_FILES")){
3372  nVolumeOutputFiles = 3;
3373  VolumeOutputFiles = new OUTPUT_TYPE[nVolumeOutputFiles];
3374  VolumeOutputFiles[0] = OUTPUT_TYPE::RESTART_BINARY;
3375  VolumeOutputFiles[1] = OUTPUT_TYPE::PARAVIEW_XML;
3376  VolumeOutputFiles[2] = OUTPUT_TYPE::SURFACE_PARAVIEW_XML;
3377  }
3378 
3379  /*--- Set the default output frequencies ---*/
3380  if (!OptionIsSet("OUTPUT_WRT_FREQ")){
3381  nVolumeOutputFrequencies = nVolumeOutputFiles;
3382  VolumeOutputFrequencies = new unsigned long [nVolumeOutputFrequencies];
3383 
3384  /*--- Using default frequency of 250 for all files when steady, and 1 for unsteady. ---*/
3385  for (auto iVolumeFreq = 0; iVolumeFreq < nVolumeOutputFrequencies; iVolumeFreq++){
3386  VolumeOutputFrequencies[iVolumeFreq] = Time_Domain ? 1 : 250;
3387  }
3388  } else if (nVolumeOutputFrequencies < nVolumeOutputFiles) {
3389  /*--- If there are fewer frequencies than files, repeat the last frequency.
3390  * This is useful to define 1 frequency for the restart file and 1 frequency for all the visualization files. ---*/
3391  auto* newFrequencies = new unsigned long[nVolumeOutputFiles];
3392  for (unsigned short i = 0; i < nVolumeOutputFrequencies; ++i) {
3393  newFrequencies[i] = VolumeOutputFrequencies[i];
3394  }
3395  for (auto i = nVolumeOutputFrequencies; i < nVolumeOutputFiles; ++i) {
3396  newFrequencies[i] = newFrequencies[i-1];
3397  }
3398  delete [] VolumeOutputFrequencies;
3399  VolumeOutputFrequencies = newFrequencies;
3400  nVolumeOutputFrequencies = nVolumeOutputFiles;
3401  }
3402 
3403  /*--- Check if SU2 was build with TecIO support, as that is required for Tecplot Binary output. ---*/
3404 #ifndef HAVE_TECIO
3405  for (unsigned short iVolumeFile = 0; iVolumeFile < nVolumeOutputFiles; iVolumeFile++){
3406  if (VolumeOutputFiles[iVolumeFile] == OUTPUT_TYPE::TECPLOT_BINARY ||
3407  VolumeOutputFiles[iVolumeFile] == OUTPUT_TYPE::SURFACE_TECPLOT_BINARY) {
3408  SU2_MPI::Error(string("Tecplot binary file requested in option OUTPUT_FILES but SU2 was built without TecIO support.\n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3409  }
3410  }
3411 #endif
3412 
3413  /*--- Check if SU2 was build with CGNS support, as that is required for CGNS output. ---*/
3414 #ifndef HAVE_CGNS
3415  for (unsigned short iVolumeFile = 0; iVolumeFile < nVolumeOutputFiles; iVolumeFile++) {
3416  if (VolumeOutputFiles[iVolumeFile] == OUTPUT_TYPE::CGNS ||
3417  VolumeOutputFiles[iVolumeFile] == OUTPUT_TYPE::SURFACE_CGNS) {
3418  SU2_MPI::Error(string("CGNS file requested in option OUTPUT_FILES but SU2 was built without CGNS support.\n"),CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3419  }
3420  }
3421 #endif
3422 
3423  /*--- Check if CoolProp is used with non-dimensionalization. ---*/
3424  if (Kind_FluidModel == COOLPROP && Ref_NonDim != DIMENSIONAL) {
3425  SU2_MPI::Error("CoolProp can not be used with non-dimensionalization.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3426  }
3427 
3428  /*--- STL_BINARY output not implemented yet, but already a value in option_structure.hpp---*/
3429  for (unsigned short iVolumeFile = 0; iVolumeFile < nVolumeOutputFiles; iVolumeFile++) {
3430  if (VolumeOutputFiles[iVolumeFile] == OUTPUT_TYPE::STL_BINARY){
3431  SU2_MPI::Error(string("OUTPUT_FILES: 'STL_BINARY' output not implemented. Use 'STL' for ASCII output.\n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3432  }
3433  if (val_nDim == 2 && (VolumeOutputFiles[iVolumeFile] == OUTPUT_TYPE::STL_ASCII || VolumeOutputFiles[iVolumeFile] == OUTPUT_TYPE::STL_BINARY)) {
3434  SU2_MPI::Error(string("OUTPUT_FILES: 'STL(_BINARY)' output only reasonable for 3D cases.\n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3435  }
3436  }
3437 
3438  /*--- Check if MESH_QUALITY is requested in VOLUME_OUTPUT and set the config boolean accordingly. ---*/
3439  Wrt_MeshQuality = false;
3440  for (unsigned short iField = 0; iField < nVolumeOutput; iField++) {
3441  if(VolumeOutput[iField].find("MESH_QUALITY") != string::npos) {
3442  Wrt_MeshQuality = true;
3443  }
3444  }
3445 
3446  /*--- Check if MULTIGRID is requested in VOLUME_OUTPUT and set the config boolean accordingly. ---*/
3447  Wrt_MultiGrid = false;
3448  for (unsigned short iField = 0; iField < nVolumeOutput; iField++) {
3449  if(VolumeOutput[iField].find("MULTIGRID") != string::npos) {
3450  Wrt_MultiGrid = true;
3451  }
3452  }
3453 
3454  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES && Kind_Turb_Model != TURB_MODEL::NONE){
3455  SU2_MPI::Error("KIND_TURB_MODEL must be NONE if SOLVER= NAVIER_STOKES", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3456  }
3457  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES && Kind_Turb_Model != TURB_MODEL::NONE){
3458  SU2_MPI::Error("KIND_TURB_MODEL must be NONE if SOLVER= INC_NAVIER_STOKES", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3459  }
3460  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::RANS && Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::NONE){
3461  SU2_MPI::Error("A turbulence model must be specified with KIND_TURB_MODEL if SOLVER= RANS", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3462  }
3463  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS && Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::NONE){
3464  SU2_MPI::Error("A turbulence model must be specified with KIND_TURB_MODEL if SOLVER= INC_RANS", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3465  }
3466 
3467  /*--- Postprocess SST_OPTIONS into structure. ---*/
3468  if (Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::SST) {
3469  sstParsedOptions = ParseSSTOptions(SST_Options, nSST_Options, rank);
3470  } else if (Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::SA) {
3471  saParsedOptions = ParseSAOptions(SA_Options, nSA_Options, rank);
3472  }
3473 
3474  /*--- Check if turbulence model can be used for AXISYMMETRIC case---*/
3475  if (Axisymmetric && Kind_Turb_Model != TURB_MODEL::NONE && Kind_Turb_Model != TURB_MODEL::SST){
3476  SU2_MPI::Error("Axisymmetry is currently only supported for KIND_TURB_MODEL chosen as SST", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3477  }
3478 
3479  /*--- Postprocess LM_OPTIONS into structure. ---*/
3480  if (Kind_Trans_Model == TURB_TRANS_MODEL::LM) {
3481  lmParsedOptions = ParseLMOptions(LM_Options, nLM_Options, rank, Kind_Turb_Model);
3482 
3483  /*--- Check if problem is 2D and LM2015 has been selected ---*/
3484  if (lmParsedOptions.LM2015 && val_nDim == 2) {
3485  SU2_MPI::Error("LM2015 is available only for 3D problems", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3486  }
3487  }
3488 
3489  /*--- Set the boolean Wall_Functions equal to true if there is a
3490  definition for the wall founctions ---*/
3491 
3492  Wall_Functions = false;
3493  if (nMarker_WallFunctions > 0) {
3494  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_WallFunctions; iMarker++) {
3495  if (Kind_WallFunctions[iMarker] != WALL_FUNCTIONS::NONE)
3496  Wall_Functions = true;
3497 
3498  if ((Kind_WallFunctions[iMarker] == WALL_FUNCTIONS::ADAPTIVE_FUNCTION) ||
3499  (Kind_WallFunctions[iMarker] == WALL_FUNCTIONS::SCALABLE_FUNCTION) ||
3500  (Kind_WallFunctions[iMarker] == WALL_FUNCTIONS::NONEQUILIBRIUM_MODEL))
3501  SU2_MPI::Error(string("For RANS problems, use NONE, STANDARD_WALL_FUNCTION or EQUILIBRIUM_WALL_MODEL.\n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3502 
3503  if (Kind_WallFunctions[iMarker] == WALL_FUNCTIONS::STANDARD_FUNCTION) {
3504  if (!((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::RANS) || (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS)))
3505  SU2_MPI::Error(string("Wall model STANDARD_FUNCTION only available for RANS or INC_RANS.\n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3506  if (nRough_Wall != 0)
3507  SU2_MPI::Error(string("Wall model STANDARD_FUNCTION and WALL_ROUGHNESS migh not be compatible. Checking required!\n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3508  }
3509 
3510  }
3511  }
3512 
3513  /*--- Initialize the AoA and Sideslip variables for the incompressible
3514  solver. This is typically unused (often internal flows). Also fixed CL
3515  mode for incompressible flows is not implemented ---*/
3516 
3517  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER ||
3518  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES ||
3519  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) {
3520 
3521  /*--- Compute x-velocity with a safegaurd for 0.0. ---*/
3522 
3523  su2double Vx = 1e-10;
3524  if (vel_init[0] != 0.0) {
3525  Vx = vel_init[0];
3526  }
3527 
3528  /*--- Compute the angle-of-attack and sideslip. ---*/
3529 
3530  su2double alpha = 0.0, beta = 0.0;
3531  if (val_nDim == 2) {
3532  alpha = atan(vel_init[1]/Vx)*180.0/PI_NUMBER;
3533  } else {
3534  alpha = atan(vel_init[2]/Vx)*180.0/PI_NUMBER;
3535  beta = atan(vel_init[1]/Vx)*180.0/PI_NUMBER;
3536  }
3537 
3538  /*--- Set alpha and beta in the config class. ---*/
3539 
3540  SetAoA(alpha);
3541  SetAoS(beta);
3542 
3543  if (Fixed_CL_Mode) {
3544  SU2_MPI::Error(string("Fixed CL mode not implemented for the incompressible solver. \n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3545  }
3546 
3547  /*--- Inc CHT simulation, but energy equation of fluid is inactive. ---*/
3548  if (Multizone_Problem && (nMarker_CHTInterface > 0) && !Energy_Equation)
3549  SU2_MPI::Error(string("You probably want to set INC_ENERGY_EQUATION= YES for the fluid solver. \n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3550  }
3551 
3552  /*--- By default, in 2D we should use TWOD_AIRFOIL (independenly from the input file) ---*/
3553 
3554  if (val_nDim == 2) Geo_Description = TWOD_AIRFOIL;
3555 
3556  /*--- Store the SU2 module that we are executing. ---*/
3557 
3558  Kind_SU2 = val_software;
3559 
3560  /*--- Set limiter for no MUSCL reconstructions ---*/
3561 
3562  if (!MUSCL_Flow || (Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow == SPACE_CENTERED)) Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow = LIMITER::NONE;
3563  if (!MUSCL_Turb || (Kind_ConvNumScheme_Turb == SPACE_CENTERED)) Kind_SlopeLimit_Turb = LIMITER::NONE;
3564  if (!MUSCL_Species || (Kind_ConvNumScheme_Species == SPACE_CENTERED)) Kind_SlopeLimit_Species = LIMITER::NONE;
3565  if (!MUSCL_AdjFlow || (Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjFlow == SPACE_CENTERED)) Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjFlow = LIMITER::NONE;
3566  if (!MUSCL_AdjTurb || (Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjTurb == SPACE_CENTERED)) Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjTurb = LIMITER::NONE;
3567 
3568  /*--- Set the default for thrust in ActDisk ---*/
3569 
3570  if ((Kind_ActDisk == NET_THRUST) || (Kind_ActDisk == BC_THRUST)
3571  || (Kind_ActDisk == DRAG_MINUS_THRUST) || (Kind_ActDisk == MASSFLOW)
3572  || (Kind_ActDisk == POWER))
3573  ActDisk_Jump = RATIO;
3574 
3575  /*--- Error-catching and automatic array adjustments for objective, marker, and weights arrays --- */
3576 
3577  /*--- If Kind_Obj has not been specified, these arrays need to take a default --*/
3578 
3579  if (Weight_ObjFunc == nullptr && Kind_ObjFunc == nullptr) {
3580  Kind_ObjFunc = new unsigned short[1];
3581  Kind_ObjFunc[0] = DRAG_COEFFICIENT;
3582  Weight_ObjFunc = new su2double[1];
3583  Weight_ObjFunc[0] = 1.0;
3584  nObj=1;
3585  nObjW=1;
3586  }
3587 
3588  /*--- Maker sure that arrays are the same length ---*/
3589 
3590  if (nObj>0) {
3591  if (nMarker_Monitoring!=nObj && Marker_Monitoring!= nullptr) {
3592  if (nMarker_Monitoring==1) {
3593  /*-- If only one marker was listed with multiple objectives, set that marker as the marker for each objective ---*/
3594  nMarker_Monitoring = nObj;
3595  string marker = Marker_Monitoring[0];
3596  delete[] Marker_Monitoring;
3597  Marker_Monitoring = new string[nMarker_Monitoring];
3598  for (iMarker=0; iMarker<nMarker_Monitoring; iMarker++)
3599  Marker_Monitoring[iMarker] = marker;
3600  }
3601  else if(nObj==1){
3602  /*--- If one objective and more than one marker: repeat objective over each marker, evenly weighted ---*/
3603  unsigned int obj = Kind_ObjFunc[0];
3604  su2double wt=1.0;
3605  delete[] Kind_ObjFunc;
3606  if (Weight_ObjFunc!=nullptr){
3607  wt = Weight_ObjFunc[0];
3608  delete[] Weight_ObjFunc;
3609  }
3610  Kind_ObjFunc = new short unsigned int[nMarker_Monitoring];
3611  Weight_ObjFunc = new su2double[nMarker_Monitoring];
3612  for (unsigned short iObj=0; iObj<nMarker_Monitoring; iObj++){
3613  Kind_ObjFunc[iObj] = obj;
3614  Weight_ObjFunc[iObj] = wt;
3615  }
3616  nObjW = nObj;
3617  }
3618  else if(nObj>1) {
3619  SU2_MPI::Error("When using more than one OBJECTIVE_FUNCTION, MARKER_MONITORING must be the same length or length 1.\n"
3620  "For multiple surfaces per objective, either use one objective or list the objective multiple times.\n"
3621  "For multiple objectives per marker either use one marker or list the marker multiple times.\n"
3622  "Similar rules apply for multi-objective optimization using OPT_OBJECTIVE rather than OBJECTIVE_FUNCTION.",
3623  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3624  }
3625  }
3626  }
3627 
3628  /*-- Correct for case where Weight_ObjFunc has not been provided or has length < kind_objfunc---*/
3629 
3630  if (nObjW<nObj) {
3631  if (Weight_ObjFunc!= nullptr && nObjW>1) {
3632  SU2_MPI::Error("The option OBJECTIVE_WEIGHT must either have the same length as OBJECTIVE_FUNCTION,\n"
3633  "be lenght 1, or be deleted from the config file (equal weights will be applied).", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3634  }
3635  Weight_ObjFunc = new su2double[nObj];
3636  for (unsigned short iObj=0; iObj<nObj; iObj++)
3637  Weight_ObjFunc[iObj] = 1.0;
3638  }
3639 
3640  /*--- One final check for multi-objective with the set of objectives
3641  that are not counted per-surface. We will disable multi-objective here. ---*/
3642 
3643  if (nObj > 1) {
3644  unsigned short Obj_0 = Kind_ObjFunc[0];
3645  for (unsigned short iObj=1; iObj<nObj; iObj++){
3646  switch(Kind_ObjFunc[iObj]) {
3647  case INVERSE_DESIGN_PRESSURE:
3648  case INVERSE_DESIGN_HEATFLUX:
3649  case THRUST_COEFFICIENT:
3650  case TORQUE_COEFFICIENT:
3651  case FIGURE_OF_MERIT:
3652  case SURFACE_TOTAL_PRESSURE:
3653  case SURFACE_STATIC_PRESSURE:
3654  case SURFACE_STATIC_TEMPERATURE:
3655  case SURFACE_MASSFLOW:
3656  case SURFACE_UNIFORMITY:
3657  case SURFACE_SECONDARY:
3658  case SURFACE_MOM_DISTORTION:
3659  case SURFACE_SECOND_OVER_UNIFORM:
3660  case SURFACE_PRESSURE_DROP:
3661  case SURFACE_SPECIES_0:
3662  case SURFACE_SPECIES_VARIANCE:
3663  case CUSTOM_OBJFUNC:
3664  if (Kind_ObjFunc[iObj] != Obj_0) {
3665  SU2_MPI::Error("The following objectives can only be used for the first surface in a multi-objective \n"
3666  "problem or as a single objective applied to multiple monitoring markers:\n"
3667  "INVERSE_DESIGN_PRESSURE, INVERSE_DESIGN_HEATFLUX, THRUST_COEFFICIENT, TORQUE_COEFFICIENT\n"
3668  "FIGURE_OF_MERIT, SURFACE_TOTAL_PRESSURE, SURFACE_STATIC_PRESSURE, SURFACE_MASSFLOW\n"
3669  "SURFACE_UNIFORMITY, SURFACE_SECONDARY, SURFACE_MOM_DISTORTION, SURFACE_SECOND_OVER_UNIFORM\n"
3670  "SURFACE_PRESSURE_DROP, SURFACE_STATIC_TEMPERATURE, SURFACE_SPECIES_0\n"
3671  "SURFACE_SPECIES_VARIANCE, CUSTOM_OBJFUNC.\n", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3672  }
3673  break;
3674  default:
3675  break;
3676  }
3677  }
3678  }
3679 
3680  if (Kind_ObjFunc[0] == CUSTOM_OBJFUNC && CustomObjFunc.empty() && !Multizone_Problem) {
3681  SU2_MPI::Error("The expression for the custom objective function was not set.\n"
3682  "For example, CUSTOM_OBJFUNC= LIFT/DRAG", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3683  }
3684 
3685  /*--- Check for unsteady problem ---*/
3686 
3687  if ((TimeMarching == TIME_MARCHING::TIME_STEPPING ||
3688  TimeMarching == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_1ST ||
3689  TimeMarching == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_2ND) && !Time_Domain){
3690  SU2_MPI::Error("TIME_DOMAIN must be set to YES if TIME_MARCHING is "
3691  "TIME_STEPPING, DUAL_TIME_STEPPING-1ST_ORDER or DUAL_TIME_STEPPING-2ND_ORDER", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3692  }
3693 
3694  if (Time_Domain){
3695  Delta_UnstTime = Time_Step;
3696  Delta_DynTime = Time_Step;
3697 
3698  if (TimeMarching == TIME_MARCHING::TIME_STEPPING){ InnerIter = 1; }
3699 
3700  /*--- Set History write freq for inner and outer iteration to zero by default, so only time iterations write. ---*/
3701  if (!OptionIsSet("HISTORY_WRT_FREQ_INNER")) { HistoryWrtFreq[2] = 0; }
3702  if (!OptionIsSet("HISTORY_WRT_FREQ_OUTER")) { HistoryWrtFreq[1] = 0; }
3703 
3704  if (Restart == NO) {
3705  Restart_Iter = 0;
3706  } else {
3707  if(nTimeIter <= Restart_Iter) SU2_MPI::Error("TIME_ITER must be larger than RESTART_ITER.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3708  }
3709 
3710  /*--- WINDOW_START_ITER must be larger than or equal to: RESTART_ITER. Otherwise, the running average is wrong. ---*/
3711  if (OptionIsSet("WINDOW_START_ITER")) {
3712  if (StartWindowIteration < Restart_Iter) {
3713  SU2_MPI::Error("WINDOW_START_ITER must be larger than or equal to: RESTART_ITER!", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3714  }
3715  } else {
3716  /*--- Enforced default behavior: start of the window is the first new iteration. ---*/
3717  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "WARNING: Setting WINDOW_START_ITER = RESTART_ITER for meaningful running average.\n";
3718  StartWindowIteration = Restart_Iter;
3719  }
3720 
3721  if (Time_Step <= 0.0 && Unst_CFL == 0.0){ SU2_MPI::Error("Invalid value for TIME_STEP.", CURRENT_FUNCTION); }
3722  } else {
3723  nTimeIter = 1;
3724  Time_Step = 0;
3725 
3726  /*--- Entry 0 corresponds to unsteady simulation so for steady simulation are just set to 1. ---*/
3727  ScreenWrtFreq[0] = 1;
3728  HistoryWrtFreq[0] = 1;
3729 
3730  if (TimeMarching != TIME_MARCHING::HARMONIC_BALANCE) { TimeMarching = TIME_MARCHING::STEADY; }
3731  }
3732 
3733  if (Time_Domain && !GetWrt_Restart_Overwrite()){
3734  SU2_MPI::Error("Appending iterations to the filename (WRT_RESTART_OVERWRITE=NO) is incompatible with transient problems.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3735  }
3736  if (Time_Domain && !GetWrt_Surface_Overwrite()){
3737  SU2_MPI::Error("Appending iterations to the filename (WRT_SURFACE_OVERWRITE=NO) is incompatible with transient problems.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3738  }
3739  if (Time_Domain && !GetWrt_Volume_Overwrite()){
3740  SU2_MPI::Error("Appending iterations to the filename (WRT_VOLUME_OVERWRITE=NO) is incompatible with transient problems.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3741  }
3742 
3743 
3744  /*--- Ensure that Discard_InFiles is false, owerwise the gradient could be wrong ---*/
3745 
3746  if ((ContinuousAdjoint || DiscreteAdjoint) && Fixed_CL_Mode && !Eval_dOF_dCX)
3747  Discard_InFiles = false;
3748 
3749  /*--- Deactivate the multigrid in the adjoint problem ---*/
3750 
3751  if ((ContinuousAdjoint && !MG_AdjointFlow) ||
3752  (TimeMarching == TIME_MARCHING::TIME_STEPPING)) { nMGLevels = 0; }
3753 
3754  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::EULER ||
3755  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES ||
3756  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::RANS ||
3757  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_EULER ||
3758  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_NAVIER_STOKES ||
3759  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_EULER ||
3760  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_NAVIER_STOKES ||
3761  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_RANS ||
3762  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_LES){
3763  Kind_Regime = ENUM_REGIME::COMPRESSIBLE;
3764  } else if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER ||
3765  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES ||
3766  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS){
3767  Kind_Regime = ENUM_REGIME::INCOMPRESSIBLE;
3768  } else {
3769  Kind_Regime = ENUM_REGIME::NO_FLOW;
3770  }
3771 
3772  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && ContinuousAdjoint && (Ref_NonDim == DIMENSIONAL) && (Kind_SU2 == SU2_COMPONENT::SU2_CFD)) {
3773  cout << "WARNING: The adjoint solver should use a non-dimensional flow solution." << endl;
3774  }
3775 
3776  /*--- Initialize non-physical points/reconstructions to zero ---*/
3777 
3778  Nonphys_Points = 0;
3779  Nonphys_Reconstr = 0;
3780 
3781  /*--- Set the number of external iterations to 1 for the steady state problem ---*/
3782 
3783  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_ELASTICITY) {
3784  nMGLevels = 0;
3785  if (Kind_Struct_Solver == STRUCT_DEFORMATION::SMALL){
3786  MinLogResidual = log10(Linear_Solver_Error);
3787  }
3788  }
3789 
3790  Radiation = (Kind_Radiation != RADIATION_MODEL::NONE);
3791 
3792  /*--- Check for unsupported features. ---*/
3793 
3794  if ((Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::EULER && Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES && Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::RANS) && (TimeMarching == TIME_MARCHING::HARMONIC_BALANCE)){
3795  SU2_MPI::Error("Harmonic Balance not yet implemented for the incompressible solver.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3796  }
3797 
3798  /*--- Check for Fluid model consistency ---*/
3799 
3800  if (standard_air) {
3801  if (Gamma != 1.4 || Gas_Constant != 287.058) {
3802  Gamma = 1.4;
3803  Gas_Constant = 287.058;
3804  }
3805  }
3806 
3807 /*--- Set default values for various fluid properties. ---*/
3808 
3809  const su2double Molecular_Weight_Default = 28.96;
3810  const su2double Mu_Constant_Default = (SystemMeasurements == SI) ? 1.716E-5 : (1.716E-5 / 47.88025898);
3811  const su2double Mu_Ref_Default = Mu_Constant_Default;
3812  const su2double Mu_Temperature_Ref_Default = (SystemMeasurements == SI) ? 273.15 : (273.15 * 1.8);
3813  const su2double Mu_S_Default = (SystemMeasurements == SI) ? 110.4 : (110.4 * 1.8);
3814  const su2double Specific_Heat_Cp_Default = 1004.703;
3815  const su2double Thermal_Conductivity_Constant_Default = (SystemMeasurements == SI) ? 2.57E-2 : (2.57E-2 * 0.577789317);
3816  const su2double Prandtl_Lam_Default = 0.72;
3817  const su2double Prandtl_Turb_Default = 0.9;
3818  const su2double Lewis_Number_Default = 1.0;
3819 
3820  auto SetDefaultIfEmpty = [](su2double*& array, unsigned short& size, const su2double& default_val) {
3821  if (array == nullptr) {
3822  array = new su2double[1];
3823  array[0] = default_val;
3824  size = 1;
3825  }
3826  };
3827 
3828  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Molecular_Weight, nMolecular_Weight, Molecular_Weight_Default);
3829  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Specific_Heat_Cp, nSpecific_Heat_Cp, Specific_Heat_Cp_Default);
3830  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Mu_Constant, nMu_Constant, Mu_Constant_Default);
3831  if (Mu_Ref == nullptr && Mu_Temperature_Ref == nullptr && Mu_S == nullptr) {
3832  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Mu_Ref, nMu_Ref, Mu_Ref_Default);
3833  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Mu_Temperature_Ref, nMu_Temperature_Ref, Mu_Temperature_Ref_Default);
3834  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Mu_S, nMu_S, Mu_S_Default);
3835  }
3836  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Thermal_Conductivity_Constant, nThermal_Conductivity_Constant,
3837  Thermal_Conductivity_Constant_Default);
3838  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Prandtl_Lam, nPrandtl_Lam, Prandtl_Lam_Default);
3839  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Prandtl_Turb, nPrandtl_Turb, Prandtl_Turb_Default);
3840  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Constant_Lewis_Number, nConstant_Lewis_Number, Lewis_Number_Default);
3841 
3842  /*--- Check whether inputs for FLUID_MIXTURE are correctly specified. ---*/
3843 
3844  if (Kind_FluidModel == FLUID_MIXTURE) {
3845  /*--- Check whether the number of entries of each specified fluid property equals the number of transported scalar
3846  equations solved + 1. nMolecular_Weight and nSpecific_Heat_Cp are used because it is required for the fluid mixing models.
3847  * Cp is required in case of MIXTURE_FLUID_MODEL because the energy equation needs to be active.--- */
3848  if (nMolecular_Weight != nSpecies_Init + 1 || nSpecific_Heat_Cp != nSpecies_Init + 1) {
3849  SU2_MPI::Error(
3850  "The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the number of entries for MOLECULAR_WEIGHT and SPECIFIC_HEAT_CP,\n"
3851  "to be equal to the number of entries of SPECIES_INIT + 1",
3852  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3853  }
3854  /*--- Check whether the density model used is correct, in the case of FLUID_MIXTURE the density model must be
3855  VARIABLE. Otherwise, if the density model is CONSTANT, the scalars will not have influence the mixture density
3856  and it will remain constant through the complete domain. --- */
3857  if (Kind_DensityModel != INC_DENSITYMODEL::VARIABLE) {
3858  SU2_MPI::Error("The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the INC_DENSITY_MODEL option to be VARIABLE",
3859  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3860  }
3861 
3862  switch (Kind_ViscosityModel) {
3863  case VISCOSITYMODEL::CONSTANT:
3864  if (nMu_Constant != nSpecies_Init + 1) {
3865  SU2_MPI::Error(
3866  "The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the number of entries for MU_CONSTANT,\n"
3867  "to be equal to the number of entries of SPECIES_INIT + 1",
3868  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3869  }
3870  break;
3871  case VISCOSITYMODEL::SUTHERLAND:
3872  if ((nMu_Ref != nSpecies_Init + 1) || (nMu_Temperature_Ref != nSpecies_Init + 1) ||
3873  (nMu_S != nSpecies_Init + 1)) {
3874  SU2_MPI::Error(
3875  "The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the number of entries for MU_REF, MU_T_REF and "
3876  "SUTHERLAND_CONSTANT,\n"
3877  "to be equal to the number of entries of SPECIES_INIT + 1",
3878  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3879  }
3880  break;
3881  default:
3882  if (nSpecies_Init + 1 != 1) SU2_MPI::Error("Viscosity model not available.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3883  break;
3884  }
3885 
3886  switch (Kind_ConductivityModel) {
3887  case CONDUCTIVITYMODEL::CONSTANT:
3888  if ((Kind_ConductivityModel_Turb == CONDUCTIVITYMODEL_TURB::CONSTANT_PRANDTL) &&
3889  (Kind_Turb_Model != TURB_MODEL::NONE)) {
3890  if ((nThermal_Conductivity_Constant != nSpecies_Init + 1) || (nPrandtl_Turb != nSpecies_Init + 1)) {
3891  SU2_MPI::Error(
3892  "The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the number of entries for THERMAL_CONDUCTIVITY_CONSTANT and "
3893  "PRANDTL_TURB,\n"
3894  "to be equal to the number of entries of SPECIES_INIT + 1",
3895  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3896  }
3897  } else {
3898  if (nThermal_Conductivity_Constant != nSpecies_Init + 1) {
3899  SU2_MPI::Error(
3900  "The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the number of entries for THERMAL_CONDUCTIVITY_CONSTANT,\n"
3901  "to be equal to the number of entries of SPECIES_INIT + 1",
3902  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3903  }
3904  }
3905  break;
3906  case CONDUCTIVITYMODEL::CONSTANT_PRANDTL:
3907  if (Kind_ConductivityModel_Turb == CONDUCTIVITYMODEL_TURB::CONSTANT_PRANDTL) {
3908  if ((nPrandtl_Lam != nSpecies_Init + 1) || (nPrandtl_Turb != nSpecies_Init + 1)) {
3909  SU2_MPI::Error(
3910  "The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the number of entries for PRANDTL_LAM and PRANDTL_TURB,\n"
3911  "to be equal to the number of entries of SPECIES_INIT + 1",
3912  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3913  }
3914  } else {
3915  if (nPrandtl_Lam != nSpecies_Init + 1) {
3916  SU2_MPI::Error(
3917  "The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the number of entries for PRANDTL_LAM,\n"
3918  "to be equal to the number of entries of SPECIES_INIT + 1",
3919  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3920  }
3921  }
3922  break;
3923  default:
3924  if (nSpecies_Init + 1 != 1) SU2_MPI::Error("Conductivity model not available.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3925  break;
3926  }
3927  }
3928 
3929  /*--- Check for Measurement System ---*/
3930 
3931  if (SystemMeasurements == US && !standard_air) {
3932  SU2_MPI::Error("Only STANDARD_AIR fluid model can be used with US Measurement System", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3933  }
3934 
3935  if (Kind_FluidModel == SU2_NONEQ && (Kind_TransCoeffModel != TRANSCOEFFMODEL::WILKE && Kind_TransCoeffModel != TRANSCOEFFMODEL::SUTHERLAND) ) {
3936  SU2_MPI::Error("Only WILKE and SUTHERLAND transport models are stable for the NEMO solver using SU2TClib. Use Mutation++ instead.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3937  }
3938 
3939  if (Kind_FluidModel == MUTATIONPP &&
3940  (Kind_TransCoeffModel != TRANSCOEFFMODEL::WILKE && Kind_TransCoeffModel != TRANSCOEFFMODEL::CHAPMANN_ENSKOG)) {
3941  SU2_MPI::Error("Only WILKE and Chapmann-Enskog transport model can be used with Mutation++ at the moment.",
3942  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3943  }

3945  if (!ideal_gas && !nemo) {
3946  if (Kind_Upwind_Flow != UPWIND::ROE && Kind_Upwind_Flow != UPWIND::HLLC && Kind_Centered_Flow != CENTERED::JST) {

3965  }

3968 
3969  if ((!ideal_gas) && (!noneq_gas)) {
3970  if (nMarker_Inlet != 0) {

3987  /*--- Check for Boundary condition available for NICF ---*/
3988 
3989  if (ideal_gas && (Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER && Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES &&
3990  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS)) {
3991  if (SystemMeasurements == US && standard_air) {
3992  if (Kind_ViscosityModel != VISCOSITYMODEL::SUTHERLAND) {

3995  }

3998  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3999  }
4000  }
4001  /*--- Check for Boundary condition option agreement ---*/
4002  if (Kind_InitOption == REYNOLDS){
4003  if ((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::RANS) && Reynolds <=0){
4004  SU2_MPI::Error("Reynolds number required for NAVIER_STOKES and RANS !!", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
4005  }
4006  }
4007 
4008  if (nKind_SurfaceMovement != nMarker_Moving) {
4009  SU2_MPI::Error("Number of SURFACE_MOVEMENT must match number of MARKER_MOVING", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
4010  }
4011 
4012  if (TimeMarching == TIME_MARCHING::TIME_STEPPING){
4013  nIter = 1;
4014  nInnerIter = 1;
4015  }
4016 
4017  if (!Multizone_Problem){
4018  ScreenWrtFreq[1] = 0;
4019  HistoryWrtFreq[1] = 0;
4020  if (!Time_Domain){
4021  /*--- If not running multizone or unsteady, INNER_ITER and ITER are interchangeable,

4523  }

4528  if (ContinuousAdjoint) {

4530  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES) Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES;
4531  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::RANS) Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_RANS;
4532  }
4533 
4534  nCFL = nMGLevels+1;
4535  CFL = new su2double[nCFL];

4542  for (iCFL = 0; iCFL < default_cfl_adapt.size(); ++iCFL) {
4543  if (iCFL < nCFL_AdaptParam) newParam[iCFL] = CFL_AdaptParam[iCFL];
4544  else newParam[iCFL] = default_cfl_adapt[iCFL];
4545  }
4546  swap(newParam, CFL_AdaptParam);
4547  delete [] newParam;
4548  nCFL_AdaptParam = default_cfl_adapt.size();
4549  }

4563  Iter_Fixed_NetThrust = SU2_TYPE::Int(su2double (Iter_Fixed_NetThrust) / CFLRedCoeff_AdjFlow);
4564  }

4631  integration points corresponding to the number of time DOFs. */
4632  vector<passivedouble> GLPoints(nTimeDOFsADER_DG), GLWeights(nTimeDOFsADER_DG);
4633  CGaussJacobiQuadrature GaussJacobi;
4634  GaussJacobi.GetQuadraturePoints(0.0, 0.0, -1.0, 1.0, GLPoints, GLWeights);
4635 
4636  TimeDOFsADER_DG = new su2double[nTimeDOFsADER_DG];
4637  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nTimeDOFsADER_DG; ++i)
4638  TimeDOFsADER_DG[i] = GLPoints[i];
4639 
4640  /* Determine the number of integration points in time, their locations
4641  on the interval [-1..1] and their integration weights. */
4642  unsigned short orderExact = ceil(Quadrature_Factor_Time_ADER_DG*(nTimeDOFsADER_DG-1));
4643  nTimeIntegrationADER_DG = orderExact/2 + 1;
4644  nTimeIntegrationADER_DG = max(nTimeIntegrationADER_DG, nTimeDOFsADER_DG);
4645  GLPoints.resize(nTimeIntegrationADER_DG);
4646  GLWeights.resize(nTimeIntegrationADER_DG);
4647  GaussJacobi.GetQuadraturePoints(0.0, 0.0, -1.0, 1.0, GLPoints, GLWeights);
4648 
4649  TimeIntegrationADER_DG = new su2double[nTimeIntegrationADER_DG];
4650  WeightsIntegrationADER_DG = new su2double[nTimeIntegrationADER_DG];
4651  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nTimeIntegrationADER_DG; ++i) {
4652  TimeIntegrationADER_DG[i] = GLPoints[i];
4653  WeightsIntegrationADER_DG[i] = GLWeights[i];
4654  }
4655  }
