4966  /*--- Incompressible solver currently limited to SI units. ---*/
4967 
4968  if ((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) && (SystemMeasurements == US)) {
4969  SU2_MPI::Error("Must use SI units for incompressible solver.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
4970  }
4971 
4972  /*--- Check that the non-dim type is valid. ---*/
4973 
4974  if ((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS)) {
4975  if ((Ref_Inc_NonDim != INITIAL_VALUES) && (Ref_Inc_NonDim != REFERENCE_VALUES) && (Ref_Inc_NonDim != DIMENSIONAL)) {
4976  SU2_MPI::Error("Incompressible non-dim. scheme invalid.\n Must use INITIAL_VALUES, REFERENCE_VALUES, or DIMENSIONAL.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
4977  }
4978  }
4979 
4980  /*--- Check that the incompressible inlets are correctly specified. ---*/
4981 
4982  if ((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) && (nMarker_Inlet != 0)) {
4983  if (nMarker_Inlet != nInc_Inlet) {
4984  SU2_MPI::Error("Inlet types for incompressible problem improperly specified.\n Use INC_INLET_TYPE= VELOCITY_INLET or PRESSURE_INLET.\n Must list a type for each inlet marker, including duplicates, e.g.,\n INC_INLET_TYPE= VELOCITY_INLET VELOCITY_INLET PRESSURE_INLET", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
4985  }
4986  for (unsigned short iInlet = 0; iInlet < nInc_Inlet; iInlet++){
4987  if ((Kind_Inc_Inlet[iInlet] != INLET_TYPE::VELOCITY_INLET) && (Kind_Inc_Inlet[iInlet] != INLET_TYPE::PRESSURE_INLET)) {
4988  SU2_MPI::Error("Undefined incompressible inlet type. VELOCITY_INLET or PRESSURE_INLET possible.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
4989  }
4990  }
4991  }
4992 
4993  /*--- Check that the incompressible inlets are correctly specified. ---*/
4994 
4995  if ((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) && (nMarker_Outlet != 0)) {
4996  if (nMarker_Outlet != nInc_Outlet) {
4997  SU2_MPI::Error("Outlet types for incompressible problem improperly specified.\n Use INC_OUTLET_TYPE= PRESSURE_OUTLET or MASS_FLOW_OUTLET.\n Must list a type for each inlet marker, including duplicates, e.g.,\n INC_OUTLET_TYPE= PRESSURE_OUTLET PRESSURE_OUTLET MASS_FLOW_OUTLET", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
4998  }
4999  for (unsigned short iInlet = 0; iInlet < nInc_Outlet; iInlet++){
5000  if ((Kind_Inc_Outlet[iInlet] != INC_OUTLET_TYPE::PRESSURE_OUTLET) && (Kind_Inc_Outlet[iInlet] != INC_OUTLET_TYPE::MASS_FLOW_OUTLET)) {
5001  SU2_MPI::Error("Undefined incompressible outlet type. PRESSURE_OUTLET or MASS_FLOW_OUTLET possible.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5002  }
5003  }
5004  }
5005 
5006  /*--- Assert that there are two markers being analyzed if the
5007  pressure drop objective function is selected. ---*/
5008 
5009  for (unsigned short iObj = 0; iObj < nObj; iObj++) {
5010  if ((Kind_ObjFunc[iObj] == SURFACE_PRESSURE_DROP) && (nMarker_Analyze < 2)) {
5011  SU2_MPI::Error("Must list the first two markers for the pressure drop objective function.\n Expected format: MARKER_ANALYZE= (outlet_name, inlet_name, ...).", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5012  }
5013  }
5014 
5015  /*--- Check feasibility for Streamwise Periodic flow ---*/
5016  if (Kind_Streamwise_Periodic != ENUM_STREAMWISE_PERIODIC::NONE) {
5017  if (Kind_Regime != ENUM_REGIME::INCOMPRESSIBLE)
5018  SU2_MPI::Error("Streamwise Periodic Flow currently only implemented for incompressible flow.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5019  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER)
5020  SU2_MPI::Error("Streamwise Periodic Flow + Incompressible Euler: Not tested yet.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5021  if (nMarker_PerBound == 0)
5022  SU2_MPI::Error("A MARKER_PERIODIC pair has to be set with KIND_STREAMWISE_PERIODIC != NONE.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5023  if (Energy_Equation && Streamwise_Periodic_Temperature && nMarker_Isothermal != 0)
5024  SU2_MPI::Error("No MARKER_ISOTHERMAL marker allowed with STREAMWISE_PERIODIC_TEMPERATURE= YES, only MARKER_HEATFLUX & MARKER_SYM.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5025  if (Ref_Inc_NonDim != DIMENSIONAL)
5026  SU2_MPI::Error("Streamwise Periodicity only works with \"INC_NONDIM= DIMENSIONAL\", the nondimensionalization with source terms doesn;t work in general.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5027  if (Axisymmetric)
5028  SU2_MPI::Error("Streamwise Periodicity terms does not not have axisymmetric corrections.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5029  if (!Energy_Equation) Streamwise_Periodic_Temperature = false;
5030  } else {
5031  /*--- Safety measure ---*/
5032  Streamwise_Periodic_Temperature = false;
5033  }
5034 
5035  /*--- Check that if the wall roughness array are compatible and set deafult values if needed. ---*/
5036  if ((nMarker_HeatFlux > 0) || (nMarker_Isothermal > 0) || (nMarker_HeatTransfer) || (nMarker_CHTInterface > 0)) {
5037 
5038  /*--- The total number of wall markers. ---*/
5039  unsigned short nWall = nMarker_HeatFlux + nMarker_Isothermal + nMarker_HeatTransfer + nMarker_CHTInterface;
5040 
5041  /*--- If no roughness is specified all walls are assumed to be smooth. ---*/
5042  if (nRough_Wall == 0) {
5043 
5044  nRough_Wall = nWall;
5045  Roughness_Height = new su2double [nWall];
5046  Kind_Wall = new WALL_TYPE [nWall];
5047  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_HeatFlux; iMarker++) {
5048  Roughness_Height[iMarker] = 0.0;
5049  Kind_Wall[iMarker] = WALL_TYPE::SMOOTH;
5050  }
5051  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_Isothermal; iMarker++) {
5052  Roughness_Height[nMarker_HeatFlux + iMarker] = 0.0;
5053  Kind_Wall[nMarker_HeatFlux + iMarker] = WALL_TYPE::SMOOTH;
5054  }
5055  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_HeatTransfer; iMarker++) {
5056  Roughness_Height[nMarker_HeatFlux + nMarker_Isothermal + iMarker] = 0.0;
5057  Kind_Wall[nMarker_HeatFlux + nMarker_Isothermal + iMarker] = WALL_TYPE::SMOOTH;
5058  }
5059  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_CHTInterface; iMarker++) {
5060  Roughness_Height[nMarker_HeatFlux + nMarker_Isothermal + nMarker_HeatTransfer + iMarker] = 0.0;
5061  Kind_Wall[nMarker_HeatFlux + nMarker_Isothermal + nMarker_HeatTransfer + iMarker] = WALL_TYPE::SMOOTH;
5062  }
5063 
5064  /*--- Check for mismatch in number of rough walls and solid walls. ---*/
5065  } else if (nRough_Wall > nWall) {
5066  SU2_MPI::Error("Mismatch in number of rough walls and solid walls. Number of rough walls cannot be more than solid walls.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5067  /*--- Check name of the marker and assign the corresponding roughness. ---*/
5068  } else {
5069  /*--- Store roughness heights in a temp array. ---*/
5070  vector<su2double> temp_rough;
5071  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nRough_Wall; iMarker++)
5072  temp_rough.push_back(Roughness_Height[iMarker]);
5073 
5074  /*--- Reallocate the roughness arrays in case not all walls are rough. ---*/
5075  delete Roughness_Height;
5076  delete Kind_Wall;
5077  Roughness_Height = new su2double [nWall];
5078  Kind_Wall = new WALL_TYPE [nWall];
5079  unsigned short jMarker, chkRough = 0;
5080 
5081  /*--- Initialize everything to smooth. ---*/
5082  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nWall; iMarker++) {
5083  Roughness_Height[iMarker] = 0.0;
5084  Kind_Wall[iMarker] = WALL_TYPE::SMOOTH;
5085  }
5086 
5087  /*--- Look through heat flux, isothermal, heat transfer and cht_interface markers and assign proper values. ---*/
5088  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nRough_Wall; iMarker++) {
5089  for (jMarker = 0; jMarker < nMarker_HeatFlux; jMarker++)
5090  if (Marker_HeatFlux[jMarker].compare(Marker_RoughWall[iMarker]) == 0) {
5091  Roughness_Height[jMarker] = temp_rough[iMarker];
5092  chkRough++;
5093  }
5094 
5095  for (jMarker = 0; jMarker < nMarker_Isothermal; jMarker++)
5096  if (Marker_Isothermal[jMarker].compare(Marker_RoughWall[iMarker]) == 0) {
5097  Roughness_Height[nMarker_HeatFlux + jMarker] = temp_rough[iMarker];
5098  chkRough++;
5099  }
5100 
5101  for (jMarker = 0; jMarker < nMarker_HeatTransfer; jMarker++)
5102  if (Marker_HeatTransfer[jMarker].compare(Marker_RoughWall[iMarker]) == 0) {
5103  Roughness_Height[nMarker_HeatFlux + nMarker_Isothermal + jMarker] = temp_rough[iMarker];
5104  chkRough++;
5105  }
5106 
5107  for (jMarker = 0; jMarker < nMarker_CHTInterface; jMarker++)
5108  if (Marker_CHTInterface[jMarker].compare(Marker_RoughWall[iMarker]) == 0) {
5109  Roughness_Height[nMarker_HeatFlux + nMarker_Isothermal + nMarker_HeatTransfer + jMarker] = temp_rough[iMarker];
5110  chkRough++;
5111  }
5112  }
5113 
5114  /*--- Update kind_wall when a non zero roughness value is specified. ---*/
5115  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nWall; iMarker++)
5116  if (Roughness_Height[iMarker] != 0.0)
5117  Kind_Wall[iMarker] = WALL_TYPE::ROUGH;
5118 
5119  /*--- Check if a non solid wall marker was specified as rough. ---*/
5120  if (chkRough != nRough_Wall)
5121  SU2_MPI::Error("Only solid walls can be rough.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5122  }
5123  }
5124 
5125  /*--- Handle default options for topology optimization ---*/
5126 
5127  if (topology_optimization && top_optim_nKernel==0) {
5128  top_optim_nKernel = 1;
5129  top_optim_kernels = new ENUM_FILTER_KERNEL [1];
5130  top_optim_kernels[0] = ENUM_FILTER_KERNEL::CONICAL_WEIGHT;
5131  }
5132 
5133  if (top_optim_nKernel != 0) {
5134  /*--- Set default value of kernel parameters ---*/
5135  if (top_optim_nKernelParams == 0) {
5136  top_optim_nKernelParams = top_optim_nKernel;
5137  top_optim_kernel_params = new su2double [top_optim_nKernel];
5138  for (unsigned short i=0; i<top_optim_nKernel; ++i) top_optim_kernel_params[i] = 1.0;
5139  }
5140  /*--- Broadcast the only value provided ---*/
5141  else if (top_optim_nKernelParams==1 && top_optim_nKernel>1) {
5142  su2double tmp = top_optim_kernel_params[0];
5143  delete [] top_optim_kernel_params;
5144  top_optim_nKernelParams = top_optim_nKernel;
5145  top_optim_kernel_params = new su2double [top_optim_nKernel];
5146  for (unsigned short i=0; i<top_optim_nKernel; ++i) top_optim_kernel_params[i] = tmp;
5147  }
5148  /*--- Numbers do not match ---*/
5149  else if (top_optim_nKernelParams != top_optim_nKernel) {
5150  SU2_MPI::Error("Different number of topology filter kernels and respective parameters.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5151  }
5152 
5153  /*--- Set default value of filter radius ---*/
5154  if (top_optim_nRadius == 0) {
5155  top_optim_nRadius = top_optim_nKernel;
5156  top_optim_filter_radius = new su2double [top_optim_nKernel];
5157  for (unsigned short i=0; i<top_optim_nKernel; ++i) top_optim_filter_radius[i] = 1.0e-6;
5158  }
5159  /*--- Broadcast the only value provided ---*/
5160  else if (top_optim_nRadius==1 && top_optim_nKernel>1) {
5161  su2double tmp = top_optim_filter_radius[0];
5162  delete [] top_optim_filter_radius;
5163  top_optim_nRadius = top_optim_nKernel;
5164  top_optim_filter_radius = new su2double [top_optim_nKernel];
5165  for (unsigned short i=0; i<top_optim_nKernel; ++i) top_optim_filter_radius[i] = tmp;
5166  }
5167  /*--- Numbers do not match ---*/
5168  else if (top_optim_nRadius != top_optim_nKernel) {
5169  SU2_MPI::Error("Different number of topology filter kernels and respective radii.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5170  }
5171  }
5172 
5173  /*--- If we are executing SU2_DOT in surface file mode, then
5174  force the projected surface sensitivity file to be written. ---*/
5175 
5176  Wrt_Projected_Sensitivity = false;
5177  if ((Kind_SU2 == SU2_COMPONENT::SU2_DOT) && (Design_Variable[0] == SURFACE_FILE)) {
5178  Wrt_Projected_Sensitivity = true;
5179  }
5180 
5181  /*--- Delay the output until exit for minimal communication mode. ---*/
5182 
5183  if (Comm_Level != COMM_FULL) {
5184 
5185  /*--- Disable the use of Comm_Level = NONE until we have properly
5186  implemented it. ---*/
5187 
5188  if (Comm_Level == COMM_NONE)
5189  SU2_MPI::Error("COMM_LEVEL = NONE not yet implemented.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5190  }
5191 
5192  /*--- Check the conductivity model. Deactivate the turbulent component
5193  if we are not running RANS. ---*/
5194 
5195  if ((Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::RANS) &&
5196  (Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_RANS) &&
5197  (Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_RANS) &&
5198  (Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) &&
5199  (Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_RANS)){
5200  Kind_ConductivityModel_Turb = CONDUCTIVITYMODEL_TURB::NONE;
5201  }
5202 
5203  /* Set a default for the size of the RECTANGLE / BOX grid sizes. */
5204 
5205  if (nMesh_Box_Size == 0) {
5206  nMesh_Box_Size = 3;
5207  Mesh_Box_Size = new short [nMesh_Box_Size];
5208  Mesh_Box_Size[0] = 33;
5209  Mesh_Box_Size[1] = 33;
5210  Mesh_Box_Size[2] = 33;
5211  } else if (nMesh_Box_Size != 3) {
5212  SU2_MPI::Error(string("MESH_BOX_SIZE specified without 3 values.\n"),
5213  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5214  }
5215 
5216  /* Force the lowest memory preconditioner when direct solvers are used. */
5217 
5218  auto isPastix = [](unsigned short kindSolver) {
5219  return kindSolver == PASTIX_LDLT || kindSolver == PASTIX_LU;
5220  };
5221 
5222  if (isPastix(Kind_Linear_Solver)) Kind_Linear_Solver_Prec = LU_SGS;
5223  if (isPastix(Kind_DiscAdj_Linear_Solver)) Kind_DiscAdj_Linear_Prec = LU_SGS;
5224  if (isPastix(Kind_Deform_Linear_Solver)) Kind_Deform_Linear_Solver_Prec = LU_SGS;
5225 
5226 
5227  if (DiscreteAdjoint) {
5228 #if !defined CODI_REVERSE_TYPE
5229  if (Kind_SU2 == SU2_COMPONENT::SU2_CFD) {
5230  SU2_MPI::Error(string("SU2_CFD: Config option MATH_PROBLEM= DISCRETE_ADJOINT requires AD support!\n") +
5231  string("Please use SU2_CFD_AD (configuration/compilation is done using the preconfigure.py script)."),
5232  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5233  }
5234 #endif
5235 
5236  /*--- Use the same linear solver on the primal as the one used in the adjoint. ---*/
5237  Kind_Linear_Solver = Kind_DiscAdj_Linear_Solver;
5238  Kind_Linear_Solver_Prec = Kind_DiscAdj_Linear_Prec;
5239 
5240  if (Time_Domain) {
5241 
5242  Restart_Flow = false;
5243 
5244  if (Unst_AdjointIter- long(nTimeIter) < 0){
5245  SU2_MPI::Error(string("Invalid iteration number requested for unsteady adjoint.\n" ) +
5246  string("Make sure EXT_ITER is larger or equal than UNST_ADJOINT_ITER."),
5247  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5248  }
5249 
5250  /*--- If the averaging interval is not set, we average over all time-steps ---*/
5251 
5252  if (Iter_Avg_Objective == 0.0) {
5253  Iter_Avg_Objective = nTimeIter;
5254  }
5255 
5256  }
5257 
5258  /*--- Note that this is deliberately done at the end of this routine! ---*/
5259  switch(Kind_Solver) {
5260  case MAIN_SOLVER::EULER:
5261  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_EULER;
5262  break;
5263  case MAIN_SOLVER::RANS:
5264  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_RANS;
5265  break;
5266  case MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES:
5267  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES;
5268  break;
5269  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER:
5270  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_EULER;
5271  break;
5272  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS:
5273  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_RANS;
5274  break;
5275  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES:
5276  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_NAVIER_STOKES;
5277  break;
5278  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_EULER :
5279  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_EULER;
5280  break;
5281  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_RANS :
5282  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_RANS;
5283  break;
5284  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_NAVIER_STOKES :
5285  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_NS;
5286  break;
5287  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_ELASTICITY:
5288  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM;
5289  break;
5290  case MAIN_SOLVER::HEAT_EQUATION:
5291  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_HEAT;
5292  break;
5293  default:
5294  break;
5295  }
5296 
5297  RampOutletPressure = false;
5298  RampRotatingFrame = false;
5299  }
5300 
5301  /* 2nd-order MUSCL is not possible for the continuous adjoint
5302  turbulence model. */
5303 
5304  if (MUSCL_AdjTurb) {
5305  SU2_MPI::Error(string("MUSCL_ADJTURB= YES not currently supported.\n") +
5306  string("Please select MUSCL_ADJTURB= NO (first-order)."),
5307  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5308  }
5309 
5310  /* Check for whether we need a second gradient method to calculate
5311  gradients for uwpind reconstruction. Set additional booleans to
5312  minimize overhead as appropriate. */
5313 
5314  if (MUSCL_Flow || MUSCL_Turb || MUSCL_Species || MUSCL_Heat || MUSCL_AdjFlow) {
5315 
5316  ReconstructionGradientRequired = true;
5317 
5318  if ((Kind_Gradient_Method_Recon == NO_GRADIENT) ||
5319  (Kind_Gradient_Method_Recon == Kind_Gradient_Method)) {
5320 
5321  /* The default behavior if no reconstruction gradient is specified
5322  is to use the same gradient as needed for the viscous/source terms
5323  without recomputation. If they are using the same method, then
5324  we also want to avoid recomputation. */
5325 
5326  ReconstructionGradientRequired = false;
5327  Kind_Gradient_Method_Recon = Kind_Gradient_Method;
5328  }
5329 
5330  }
5331 
5332  if (ReconstructionGradientRequired && GetFluidProblem() && Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow == SPACE_CENTERED)
5333  SU2_MPI::Error("For centered schemes the option NUM_METHOD_GRAD_RECON should not be set.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5334 
5335  /* Simpler boolean to control allocation of least-squares memory. */
5336 
5337  LeastSquaresRequired = false;
5338  if ((Kind_Gradient_Method_Recon == LEAST_SQUARES) ||
5339  (Kind_Gradient_Method_Recon == WEIGHTED_LEAST_SQUARES) ||
5340  (Kind_Gradient_Method == LEAST_SQUARES) ||
5341  (Kind_Gradient_Method == WEIGHTED_LEAST_SQUARES)) {
5342  LeastSquaresRequired = true;
5343  }
5344 
5345  if (Kind_Gradient_Method == LEAST_SQUARES) {
5346  SU2_MPI::Error(string("LEAST_SQUARES gradient method not allowed for viscous / source terms.\n") +
5347  string("Please select either WEIGHTED_LEAST_SQUARES or GREEN_GAUSS."),
5348  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5349  }
5350 
5351  /* Protect against using CFL adaption for non-flow or certain
5352  unsteady flow problems. */
5353 
5354  if (CFL_Adapt && !GetFluidProblem()) {
5355  SU2_MPI::Error(string("CFL adaption only available for finite-volume fluid solvers.\n") +
5356  string("Please select CFL_ADAPT = NO."),
5357  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5358  }
5359 
5360  if (CFL_Adapt && (TimeMarching == TIME_MARCHING::TIME_STEPPING)) {
5361  SU2_MPI::Error(string("CFL adaption not available for TIME_STEPPING integration.\n") +
5362  string("Please select CFL_ADAPT = NO."),
5363  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5364  }
5365 
5366  /* Protect against using incorrect CFL adaption parameters. */
5367 
5368  if (CFL_Adapt && (CFL_AdaptParam[0] > 1.0)) {
5369  SU2_MPI::Error(string("CFL adaption factor down should be less than 1.0."), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5370  }
5371 
5372  if (CFL_Adapt && (CFL_AdaptParam[1] < 1.0)) {
5373  SU2_MPI::Error(string("CFL adaption factor up should be greater than 1.0."), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5374  }
5375 
5376  if (CFL_Adapt && (CFL_AdaptParam[2] > CFL_AdaptParam[3])) {
5377  SU2_MPI::Error(string("CFL adaption minimum CFL is larger than the maximum CFL."), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5378  }
5379 
5380  /*--- 0 in the config file means "disable" which can be done using a very large group. ---*/
5381  if (edgeColorGroupSize==0) edgeColorGroupSize = 1<<30;
5382 
5383  /*--- Specifying a deforming surface requires a mesh deformation solver. ---*/
5384  if (GetSurface_Movement(DEFORMING)) Deform_Mesh = true;
5385 
5386  if (GetGasModel() == "ARGON") {monoatomic = true;}
5387  else {monoatomic = false;}
5388 
5389  /*--- Set number of Turbulence Variables. ---*/
5390  switch (TurbModelFamily(Kind_Turb_Model)) {
5391  case TURB_FAMILY::NONE:
5392  nTurbVar = 0; break;
5393  case TURB_FAMILY::SA:
5394  nTurbVar = 1; break;
5395  case TURB_FAMILY::KW:
5396  nTurbVar = 2; break;
5397  }
5398  /*--- Check whether the number of entries of the MARKER_INLET_TURBULENT equals the number of turbulent properties
5399  used for the respective turbulent model. nTurb_Properties must be equal to 1 or 2 depending on whether SA or
5400  SST model are used.--- */
5401  if (Marker_Inlet_Turb != nullptr && Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::SST && nTurb_Properties != 2)
5402  SU2_MPI::Error(
5403  "The use of MARKER_INLET_TURBULENT requires the number of entries when SST Model is used \n"
5404  "to be equal to 2 : Turbulent intensity and ratio turbulent to laminar viscosity",
5405  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5406 
5407  /*--- Checks for additional species transport. ---*/
5408  if (Kind_Species_Model == SPECIES_MODEL::SPECIES_TRANSPORT) {
5409  if (Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES &&
5410  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS &&
5411  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_NAVIER_STOKES &&
5412  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_RANS &&
5413  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES &&
5414  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::RANS &&
5415  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES &&
5416  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_RANS &&
5417  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::MULTIPHYSICS)
5418  SU2_MPI::Error("Species transport currently only available for compressible and incompressible flow.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5419 
5420  /*--- Species specific OF currently can only handle one entry in Marker_Analyze. ---*/
5421  for (unsigned short iObj = 0; iObj < nObj; iObj++) {
5422  if ((Kind_ObjFunc[iObj] == SURFACE_SPECIES_0 ||
5423  Kind_ObjFunc[iObj] == SURFACE_SPECIES_VARIANCE) &&
5424  nMarker_Analyze > 1) {
5425  SU2_MPI::Error("SURFACE_SPECIES_0 and SURFACE_SPECIES_VARIANCE currently can only handle one entry to MARKER_ANALYZE.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5426  }
5427  }
5428 
5429  if(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Species != EULER_IMPLICIT &&
5430  Kind_TimeIntScheme_Species != EULER_EXPLICIT){
5431  SU2_MPI::Error("Only TIME_DISCRE_TURB = EULER_IMPLICIT, EULER_EXPLICIT have been implemented in the scalar solver.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5432  }
5433 
5434  /*--- If Species clipping is on, make sure bounds are given by the user. ---*/
5435  if (Species_Clipping)
5436  if (!(OptionIsSet("SPECIES_CLIPPING_MIN") && OptionIsSet("SPECIES_CLIPPING_MAX")))
5437  SU2_MPI::Error("SPECIES_CLIPPING= YES requires the options SPECIES_CLIPPING_MIN/MAX to set the clipping values.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5438 
5439  /*--- Make sure a Diffusivity has been set for Constant Diffusivity. ---*/
5440  if (Kind_Diffusivity_Model == DIFFUSIVITYMODEL::CONSTANT_DIFFUSIVITY &&
5441  !(OptionIsSet("DIFFUSIVITY_CONSTANT")))
5442  SU2_MPI::Error("A DIFFUSIVITY_CONSTANT=<value> has to be set with DIFFUSIVITY_MODEL= CONSTANT_DIFFUSIVITY.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5443 
5444  /*--- Check whether the number of entries of the constant Lewis number equals the number of transported scalar
5445  equations solved. nConstant_Lewis_Number is used because it is required for the diffusivity fluid mixing
5446  models--- */
5447  if (Kind_Diffusivity_Model == DIFFUSIVITYMODEL::CONSTANT_LEWIS && nConstant_Lewis_Number != nSpecies_Init)
5448  SU2_MPI::Error(
5449  "The use of CONSTANT_LEWIS requires the number of entries for CONSTANT_LEWIS_NUMBER ,\n"
5450  "to be equal to the number of entries of SPECIES_INIT",
5451  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5452 
5453  // Helper function that checks scalar variable bounds,
5454  auto checkScalarBounds = [&](su2double scalar, string name, su2double lowerBound, su2double upperBound) {
5455  if (scalar < lowerBound || scalar > upperBound)
5456  SU2_MPI::Error(string("Variable: ") + name + string(", is out of bounds."), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5457  };
5458 
5459  /*--- Some options have to provide as many entries as there are additional species equations. ---*/
5460  /*--- Fill a vector with the entires and then check if each element is equal to the first one. ---*/
5461  std::vector<unsigned short> nSpecies_options;
5462  nSpecies_options.push_back(nSpecies_Init);
5463  if (Species_Clipping)
5464  nSpecies_options.insert(nSpecies_options.end(), {nSpecies_Clipping_Min, nSpecies_Clipping_Max});
5465  if (nMarker_Inlet_Species > 0)
5466  nSpecies_options.push_back(nSpecies_per_Inlet);
5467  // Add more options for size check here.
5468 
5469  /*--- nSpecies_Init is the master, but it simply checks for consistency. ---*/
5470  for (auto elem : nSpecies_options)
5471  if (nSpecies_options[0] != elem)
5472  SU2_MPI::Error("Make sure all species inputs have the same size.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5473 
5474  /*--- Once consistency is checked set the var that is used throughout the code. ---*/
5475  nSpecies = nSpecies_Init;
5476 
5477  /*--- Check whether some variables (or their sums) are in physical bounds. [0,1] for species related quantities. ---*/
5478  su2double Species_Init_Sum = 0.0;
5479  for (unsigned short iSpecies = 0; iSpecies < nSpecies; iSpecies++) {
5480  checkScalarBounds(Species_Init[iSpecies], "SPECIES_INIT individual", 0.0, 1.0);
5481  Species_Init_Sum += Species_Init[iSpecies];
5482  }
5483  checkScalarBounds(Species_Init_Sum, "SPECIES_INIT sum", 0.0, 1.0);
5484 
5485  for (unsigned short iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_Inlet_Species; iMarker++) {
5486  su2double Inlet_SpeciesVal_Sum = 0.0;
5487  for (unsigned short iSpecies = 0; iSpecies < nSpecies; iSpecies++) {
5488  checkScalarBounds(Inlet_SpeciesVal[iMarker][iSpecies], "MARKER_INLET_SPECIES individual", 0.0, 1.0);
5489  Inlet_SpeciesVal_Sum += Inlet_SpeciesVal[iMarker][iSpecies];
5490  }
5491  checkScalarBounds(Inlet_SpeciesVal_Sum, "MARKER_INLET_SPECIES sum", 0.0, 1.0);
5492  }
5493 
5494  } // species transport checks
5495 
5496  if (Kind_Regime == ENUM_REGIME::COMPRESSIBLE && GetBounded_Scalar()) {
5497  SU2_MPI::Error("BOUNDED_SCALAR discretization can only be used for incompressible problems.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5498  }
5499 }

5502

5956  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_DV[iMarker_DV])
5957  Marker_CfgFile_DV[iMarker_CfgFile] = YES;
5958  }
5959 
5960  /*--- Add an extra check for DV_MARKER to make sure that any given marker
5961  * name is recognized as an existing boundary in the problem. ---*/
5962 
5963  for (iMarker_DV = 0; iMarker_DV < nMarker_DV; iMarker_DV++) {
5964  bool found = false;

5966  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_DV[iMarker_DV]) {
5967  found = true;
5968  break;
5969  }
5970  }
5971 
5972  if(!found) {
5973  if (nZone==1)
5974  SU2_MPI::Error("DV_MARKER contains marker names that do not exist in the lists of BCs in the config file.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5975  // In case of multiple zones, the markers might appear only in zonal config and not in the Master.
5976  // A loop over all zones would need to be included which is not straight forward as this can only be
5977  // checked once all zonal configs are read.
5978  else if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
5979  cout << "Warning: DV_MARKER contains marker names that do not exist in the lists of BCs of the master config file.\n"
5980  "Make sure the marker names exist in the zonal config files" << endl;
5981  }
5982  }
5983 
5984  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++) {
5985  Marker_CfgFile_Moving[iMarker_CfgFile] = NO;
5986  for (iMarker_Moving = 0; iMarker_Moving < nMarker_Moving; iMarker_Moving++)
5987  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_Moving[iMarker_Moving])
5988  Marker_CfgFile_Moving[iMarker_CfgFile] = YES;
5989  }
5990

5993  for (iMarker_Deform_Mesh = 0; iMarker_Deform_Mesh < nMarker_Deform_Mesh; iMarker_Deform_Mesh++)
5994  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_Deform_Mesh[iMarker_Deform_Mesh])
5995  Marker_CfgFile_Deform_Mesh[iMarker_CfgFile] = YES;
5996  }

6000  for (iMarker_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane = 0; iMarker_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane < nMarker_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane; iMarker_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane++)
6001  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane[iMarker_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane])

6008  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_Fluid_Load[iMarker_Fluid_Load])
6009  Marker_CfgFile_Fluid_Load[iMarker_CfgFile] = YES;
6010  }

6027 
6028 void CConfig::SetOutput(SU2_COMPONENT val_software, unsigned short val_izone) {
6029 
6030  unsigned short iMarker_Euler, iMarker_Custom, iMarker_FarField,
6031  iMarker_SymWall, iMarker_PerBound, iMarker_NearFieldBound,
6032  iMarker_Fluid_InterfaceBound, iMarker_Inlet, iMarker_Riemann,
6033  iMarker_Deform_Mesh, iMarker_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane, iMarker_Fluid_Load,
6034  iMarker_Smoluchowski_Maxwell, iWall_Catalytic,
6035  iMarker_Giles, iMarker_Outlet, iMarker_Isothermal, iMarker_HeatFlux, iMarker_HeatTransfer,
6036  iMarker_EngineInflow, iMarker_EngineExhaust, iMarker_Displacement, iMarker_Damper,
6037  iMarker_Load, iMarker_FlowLoad, iMarker_Internal, iMarker_Monitoring,
6038  iMarker_Designing, iMarker_GeoEval, iMarker_Plotting, iMarker_Analyze, iMarker_DV, iDV_Value,
6039  iMarker_ZoneInterface, iMarker_PyCustom, iMarker_Load_Dir, iMarker_Disp_Dir, iMarker_Load_Sine, iMarker_Clamped,
6040  iMarker_Moving, iMarker_Supersonic_Inlet, iMarker_Supersonic_Outlet, iMarker_ActDiskInlet,
6041  iMarker_Emissivity,
6042  iMarker_ActDiskOutlet, iMarker_MixingPlaneInterface,
6043  iMarker_SobolevBC;
6044 
6045  bool fea = ((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_ELASTICITY) || (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM));
6046 
6047  cout << endl <<"----------------- Physical Case Definition ( Zone " << iZone << " ) -------------------" << endl;
6048  if (val_software == SU2_COMPONENT::SU2_CFD) {
6049  if (FSI_Problem)
6050  cout << "Fluid-Structure Interaction." << endl;
6051 
6052  if (DiscreteAdjoint) {
6053  cout <<"Discrete Adjoint equations using Algorithmic Differentiation\n";
6054  cout <<"based on the physical case: ";
6055  }
6056  switch (Kind_Solver) {
6057  case MAIN_SOLVER::EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_EULER:
6058  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_EULER:
6059  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_EULER:
6060  if (Kind_Regime == ENUM_REGIME::COMPRESSIBLE) cout << "Compressible Euler equations." << endl;
6061  if (Kind_Regime == ENUM_REGIME::INCOMPRESSIBLE) cout << "Incompressible Euler equations." << endl;
6062  break;
6063  case MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES:
6064  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_NAVIER_STOKES:
6065  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_NS:
6066  if (Kind_Regime == ENUM_REGIME::COMPRESSIBLE) cout << "Compressible Laminar Navier-Stokes' equations." << endl;
6067  if (Kind_Regime == ENUM_REGIME::INCOMPRESSIBLE) cout << "Incompressible Laminar Navier-Stokes' equations." << endl;
6068  break;
6069  case MAIN_SOLVER::RANS: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_RANS:
6070  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_RANS:
6071  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_RANS: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_RANS:
6072  if (Kind_Regime == ENUM_REGIME::COMPRESSIBLE) cout << "Compressible RANS equations." << endl;
6073  if (Kind_Regime == ENUM_REGIME::INCOMPRESSIBLE) cout << "Incompressible RANS equations." << endl;
6074  cout << "Turbulence model: ";
6075  switch (Kind_Turb_Model) {
6076  case TURB_MODEL::NONE: break;
6077  case TURB_MODEL::SA:
6078  switch (saParsedOptions.version) {
6079  case SA_OPTIONS::NEG:
6080  cout << "Negative-";
6081  break;
6082  case SA_OPTIONS::EDW:
6083  cout << "Edwards-";
6084  break;
6085  default:
6086  break;
6087  }
6088  cout << "Spalart-Allmaras";
6089 
6090  if (!saParsedOptions.ft2) cout << "-noft2";
6091  if (saParsedOptions.rot) cout << "-R";
6092  if (saParsedOptions.comp) cout << "-comp";
6093  if (saParsedOptions.qcr2000) cout << "-QCR2000";
6094  if (saParsedOptions.bc) cout << "-BCM";
6095  cout << endl;
6096  break;
6097  case TURB_MODEL::SST:
6098  cout << "Menter's k-omega SST";
6099  if (sstParsedOptions.version == SST_OPTIONS::V1994) cout << "-1994";
6100  else cout << "-2003";
6101  if (sstParsedOptions.modified) cout << "m";
6102  if (sstParsedOptions.sust) cout << " with sustaining terms, and";
6103 
6104  switch (sstParsedOptions.production) {
6105  case SST_OPTIONS::KL:
6106  cout << " with Kato-Launder production";
6107  break;
6108  case SST_OPTIONS::V:
6109  cout << " with Vorticity production";
6110  break;
6111  case SST_OPTIONS::UQ:
6112  cout << "\nperturbing the Reynold's Stress Matrix towards " << eig_val_comp << " component turbulence";
6113  if (uq_permute) cout << " (permuting eigenvectors)";
6114  break;
6115  default:
6116  cout << " with no production modification";
6117  break;
6118  }
6119  cout << "." << endl;
6120  break;
6121  }
6122  switch (Kind_Trans_Model) {
6123  case TURB_TRANS_MODEL::NONE: break;
6124  case TURB_TRANS_MODEL::LM: {
6125  cout << "Transition model: Langtry and Menter's 4 equation model";
6126  if (lmParsedOptions.LM2015) {
6127  cout << " w/ cross-flow corrections (2015)" << endl;
6128  } else {
6129  cout << " (2009)" << endl;
6130  }
6131  break;
6132  }
6133  }
6134  if (Kind_Trans_Model == TURB_TRANS_MODEL::LM) {
6135 
6136  cout << "Correlation Functions: ";
6137  switch (lmParsedOptions.Correlation) {
6138  case TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MALAN: cout << "Malan et al. (2009)" << endl; break;
6139  case TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::SULUKSNA: cout << "Suluksna et al. (2009)" << endl; break;
6140  case TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::KRAUSE: cout << "Krause et al. (2008)" << endl; break;
6141  case TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::KRAUSE_HYPER: cout << "Krause et al. (2008, paper)" << endl; break;
6142  case TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MEDIDA_BAEDER: cout << "Medida and Baeder (2011)" << endl; break;
6143  case TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MEDIDA: cout << "Medida PhD (2014)" << endl; break;
6144  case TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MENTER_LANGTRY: cout << "Menter and Langtry (2009)" << endl; break;
6145  case TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::DEFAULT:
6146  switch (Kind_Turb_Model) {
6147  case TURB_MODEL::SA: cout << "Malan et al. (2009)" << endl; break;
6148  case TURB_MODEL::SST: cout << "Menter and Langtry (2009)" << endl; break;
6149  case TURB_MODEL::NONE: SU2_MPI::Error("No turbulence model has been selected but LM transition model is active.", CURRENT_FUNCTION); break;
6150  }
6151  break;
6152  }
6153  }
6154  cout << "Hybrid RANS/LES: ";
6155  switch (Kind_HybridRANSLES) {
6156  case NO_HYBRIDRANSLES: cout << "No Hybrid RANS/LES" << endl; break;
6157  case SA_DES: cout << "Detached Eddy Simulation (DES97) " << endl; break;
6158  case SA_DDES: cout << "Delayed Detached Eddy Simulation (DDES) with Standard SGS" << endl; break;
6159  case SA_ZDES: cout << "Delayed Detached Eddy Simulation (DDES) with Vorticity-based SGS" << endl; break;
6160  case SA_EDDES: cout << "Delayed Detached Eddy Simulation (DDES) with Shear-layer Adapted SGS" << endl; break;
6161  }
6162  break;
6163  case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_EULER:
6164  if (Kind_Regime == ENUM_REGIME::COMPRESSIBLE) cout << "Compressible two-temperature thermochemical non-equilibrium Euler equations." << endl;
6165  if (Kind_FluidModel == SU2_NONEQ){
6166  if ((GasModel != "N2") && (GasModel != "AIR-5") && (GasModel != "AIR-7") && (GasModel != "ARGON"))
6167  SU2_MPI::Error("The GAS_MODEL given as input is not valid. Choose one of the options: N2, AIR-5, AIR-7, ARGON.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
6168  }
6169  break;
6170  case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_NAVIER_STOKES:
6171  if (Kind_Regime == ENUM_REGIME::COMPRESSIBLE) cout << "Compressible two-temperature thermochemical non-equilibrium Navier-Stokes equations." << endl;
6172  if (Kind_FluidModel == SU2_NONEQ){
6173  if ((GasModel != "N2") && (GasModel != "AIR-5") && (GasModel != "ARGON"))

6644  auto PrintLimiterInfo = [&](const LIMITER kind_limiter) {
6645  cout << "Second order integration in space, with slope limiter.\n";
6646  switch (kind_limiter) {
6647  case LIMITER::NONE:
6648  cout << "No slope-limiting method. " << endl;
6649  break;
6650  case LIMITER::VENKATAKRISHNAN:
6651  cout << "Venkatakrishnan slope-limiting method, with constant: " << Venkat_LimiterCoeff << ".\n";
6652  cout << "The reference element size is: " << RefElemLength << ". " << endl;
6653  break;
6654  case LIMITER::VENKATAKRISHNAN_WANG:
6655  cout << "Venkatakrishnan-Wang slope-limiting method, with constant: " << Venkat_LimiterCoeff << "." << endl;
6656  break;
6657  case LIMITER::BARTH_JESPERSEN:
6658  cout << "Barth-Jespersen slope-limiting method." << endl;
6659  break;
6660  case LIMITER::VAN_ALBADA_EDGE:
6661  cout << "Van Albada slope-limiting method implemented by edges." << endl;
6662  break;
6663  case LIMITER::SHARP_EDGES:
6664  cout << "Sharp edges slope-limiting method, with constant: " << Venkat_LimiterCoeff << ".\n";
6665  cout << "The reference element size is: " << RefElemLength << ".\n";
6666  cout << "The reference sharp edge distance is: " << AdjSharp_LimiterCoeff*RefElemLength*Venkat_LimiterCoeff << "." << endl;
6667  break;
6668  case LIMITER::WALL_DISTANCE:
6669  cout << "Wall distance slope-limiting method, with constant: " << Venkat_LimiterCoeff << ".\n";
6670  cout << "The reference element size is: " << RefElemLength << ".\n";
6671  cout << "The reference wall distance is: " << AdjSharp_LimiterCoeff*RefElemLength*Venkat_LimiterCoeff << "." << endl;
6672  break;
6673  default:
6674  SU2_MPI::Error("Unknown or invalid limiter type.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
6675  break;
6676  }
6677  };

7458  for (iMarker_HeatTransfer = 0; iMarker_HeatTransfer < nMarker_HeatTransfer; iMarker_HeatTransfer++) {

7460  if (iMarker_HeatTransfer < nMarker_HeatTransfer-1) BoundaryTable << " ";
7461  }
7462  BoundaryTable.PrintFooter();
7463  }
7464

7472  }

7591 bool CConfig::TokenizeString(string & str, string & option_name,
7592  vector<string> & option_value) {
7593  const string delimiters(" (){}:,\t\n\v\f\r");
7594  // check for comments or empty string
7595  string::size_type pos, last_pos;
7596  pos = str.find_first_of("%");
7597  if ( (str.length() == 0) || (pos == 0) ) {
7598  // str is empty or a comment line, so no option here
7599  return false;
7600  }
7601  if (pos != string::npos) {
7602  // remove comment at end if necessary
7603  str.erase(pos);
7604  }
7605 
7606  // look for line composed on only delimiters (usually whitespace)
7607  pos = str.find_first_not_of(delimiters);
7608  if (pos == string::npos) {
7609  return false;
7610  }
7611 
7612  // find the equals sign and split string
7613  string name_part, value_part;
7614  pos = str.find("=");
7615  if (pos == string::npos) {
7616  cerr << "Error in TokenizeString(): "
7617  << "line in the configuration file with no \"=\" sign."
7618  << endl;
7619  cout << "Look for: " << str << endl;
7620  cout << "str.length() = " << str.length() << endl;
7621  throw(-1);
7622  }
7623  name_part = str.substr(0, pos);
7624  value_part = str.substr(pos+1, string::npos);
7625  //cout << "name_part = |" << name_part << "|" << endl;
7626  //cout << "value_part = |" << value_part << "|" << endl;
7627 
7628  // the first_part should consist of one string with no interior delimiters
7629  last_pos = name_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, 0);
7630  pos = name_part.find_first_of(delimiters, last_pos);
7631  if ( (name_part.length() == 0) || (last_pos == string::npos) ) {
7632  cerr << "Error in CConfig::TokenizeString(): "
7633  << "line in the configuration file with no name before the \"=\" sign."
7634  << endl;
7635  throw(-1);
7636  }
7637  if (pos == string::npos) pos = name_part.length();
7638  option_name = name_part.substr(last_pos, pos - last_pos);
7639  last_pos = name_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, pos);
7640  if (last_pos != string::npos) {
7641  cerr << "Error in TokenizeString(): "
7642  << "two or more options before an \"=\" sign in the configuration file."
7643  << endl;
7644  throw(-1);
7645  }
7646  StringToUpperCase(option_name);
7647 
7648  //cout << "option_name = |" << option_name << "|" << endl;
7649  //cout << "pos = " << pos << ": last_pos = " << last_pos << endl;
7650 
7651  // now fill the option value vector
7652  option_value.clear();
7653  last_pos = value_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, 0);
7654 
7655  // detect a raw string
7656  if (value_part[last_pos] == '\'' && value_part.back() == '\'') {
7657  option_value.push_back(value_part.substr(last_pos+1, value_part.size()-last_pos-2));
7658  return true;
7659  }
7660 
7661  pos = value_part.find_first_of(delimiters, last_pos);
7662  while (string::npos != pos || string::npos != last_pos) {
7663  // add token to the vector<string>
7664  option_value.push_back(value_part.substr(last_pos, pos - last_pos));
7665  // skip delimiters
7666  last_pos = value_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, pos);
7667  // find next "non-delimiter"
7668  pos = value_part.find_first_of(delimiters, last_pos);
7669  }
7670  if (option_value.size() == 0) {
7671  cerr << "Error in TokenizeString(): "
7672  << "option " << option_name << " in configuration file with no value assigned."
7673  << endl;
7674  throw(-1);
7675  }
7676 
7677 #if 0
7678  cout << "option value(s) = ";
7679  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < option_value.size(); i++)
7680  cout << option_value[i] << " ";
7681  cout << endl;
7682 #endif
7683 
7684  // look for ';' DV delimiters attached to values
7685  vector<string>::iterator it;
7686  it = option_value.begin();
7687  while (it != option_value.end()) {
7688  if (it->compare(";") == 0) {
7689  it++;
7690  continue;
7691  }
7692 
7693  pos = it->find(';');
7694  if (pos != string::npos) {
7695  string before_semi = it->substr(0, pos);
7696  string after_semi= it->substr(pos+1, string::npos);
7697  if (before_semi.empty()) {
7698  *it = ";";
7699  it++;
7700  option_value.insert(it, after_semi);
7701  } else {
7702  *it = before_semi;
7703  it++;
7704  vector<string> to_insert;
7705  to_insert.push_back(";");
7706  if (!after_semi.empty())
7707  to_insert.push_back(after_semi);
7708  option_value.insert(it, to_insert.begin(), to_insert.end());
7709  }
7710  it = option_value.begin(); // go back to beginning; not efficient
7711  continue;
7712  } else {
7713  it++;
7714  }
7715  }
7716 #if 0
7717  cout << "option value(s) = ";
7718  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < option_value.size(); i++)
7719  cout << option_value[i] << " ";
7720  cout << endl;
7721 #endif
7722  // remove any consecutive ";"
7723  it = option_value.begin();
7724  bool semi_at_prev = false;
7725  while (it != option_value.end()) {
7726  if (semi_at_prev) {
7727  if (it->compare(";") == 0) {
7728  option_value.erase(it);
7729  it = option_value.begin();
7730  semi_at_prev = false;
7731  continue;
7732  }
7733  }
7734  if (it->compare(";") == 0) {
7735  semi_at_prev = true;
7736  } else {
7737  semi_at_prev = false;
7738  }
7739  it++;
7740  }
7741 
7742 #if 0
7743  cout << "option value(s) = ";
7744  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < option_value.size(); i++)
7745  cout << option_value[i] << " ";
7746  cout << endl;
7747 #endif
7748  return true;
7749 }

7751 unsigned short CConfig::GetMarker_CfgFile_TagBound(string val_marker) const {
7752 
7753  unsigned short iMarker_CfgFile;
7754 
7755  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++) {
7756  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == val_marker)
7757  return iMarker_CfgFile;
7758  }
7759  SU2_MPI::Error(string("The configuration file doesn't have any definition for marker ") + val_marker, CURRENT_FUNCTION);
7760  return 0;
7761 }

7900 bool CConfig::GetViscous_Wall(unsigned short iMarker) const {
7901 
7902  return (Marker_All_KindBC[iMarker] == HEAT_FLUX ||
7903  Marker_All_KindBC[iMarker] == ISOTHERMAL ||
7904  Marker_All_KindBC[iMarker] == HEAT_TRANSFER ||

7906  Marker_All_KindBC[iMarker] == CHT_WALL_INTERFACE);
7907 }

7909 bool CConfig::GetCatalytic_Wall(unsigned short iMarker) const {
7910 
7911  bool catalytic = false;
7912  for (unsigned short iMarker_Catalytic = 0; iMarker_Catalytic < nWall_Catalytic; iMarker_Catalytic++){
7913  string Catalytic_Tag = Wall_Catalytic[iMarker_Catalytic];
7914  if (Catalytic_Tag == Marker_All_TagBound[iMarker]) { catalytic = true; break; }
7915  }
7916 
7917  return catalytic;
7918 }

7920 bool CConfig::GetSolid_Wall(unsigned short iMarker) const {
7921 
7922  return GetViscous_Wall(iMarker) ||
7923  Marker_All_KindBC[iMarker] == EULER_WALL;
7924 }

7926 void CConfig::SetSurface_Movement(unsigned short iMarker, unsigned short kind_movement) {
7927 
7928  unsigned short* new_surface_movement = new unsigned short[nMarker_Moving + 1];
7929  string* new_marker_moving = new string[nMarker_Moving+1];
7930 
7931  for (unsigned short iMarker_Moving = 0; iMarker_Moving < nMarker_Moving; iMarker_Moving++){
7932  new_surface_movement[iMarker_Moving] = Kind_SurfaceMovement[iMarker_Moving];
7933  new_marker_moving[iMarker_Moving] = Marker_Moving[iMarker_Moving];
7934  }
7935 
7936  if (nKind_SurfaceMovement > 0){
7937  delete [] Marker_Moving;
7938  delete [] Kind_SurfaceMovement;
7939  }
7940 
7941  Kind_SurfaceMovement = new_surface_movement;
7942  Marker_Moving = new_marker_moving;
7943 
7944  Kind_SurfaceMovement[nMarker_Moving] = kind_movement;
7945  Marker_Moving[nMarker_Moving] = Marker_All_TagBound[iMarker];
7946 
7947  nMarker_Moving++;
7948  nKind_SurfaceMovement++;
7949 
7950 }
7951 
7952 CConfig::~CConfig() {
7953 
7954  unsigned long iDV, iMarker;
7955 
7956  /*--- Delete all of the option objects in the global option map ---*/
7957 
7958  for(map<string, COptionBase*>::iterator itr = option_map.begin(); itr != option_map.end(); itr++) {
7959  delete itr->second;
7960  }
7961 
7962  delete [] TimeDOFsADER_DG;
7963  delete [] TimeIntegrationADER_DG;
7964  delete [] WeightsIntegrationADER_DG;
7965 
7966  /*--- Free memory for Aeroelastic problems. ---*/
7967 
7968  delete[] Aeroelastic_pitch;
7969  delete[] Aeroelastic_plunge;
7970 
7971  /*--- Marker pointers ---*/

8169 
8170 string CConfig::GetFilename(string filename, string ext, int timeIter) const {
8171 
8172  /*--- Remove any extension --- */
8173 
8174  unsigned short lastindex = filename.find_last_of(".");
8175  filename = filename.substr(0, lastindex);
8176 
8177  /*--- Add the extension --- */
8178 
8179  filename = filename + string(ext);
8180 
8181  /*--- Append the zone number if multizone problems ---*/
8182  if (Multizone_Problem)
8183  filename = GetMultizone_FileName(filename, GetiZone(), ext);
8184 
8185  /*--- Append the zone number if multiple instance problems ---*/
8186  if (GetnTimeInstances() > 1)
8187  filename = GetMultiInstance_FileName(filename, GetiInst(), ext);
8188 
8189  /*--- Append the iteration number for unsteady problems ---*/
8190  if (GetTime_Domain()){
8191  filename = GetUnsteady_FileName(filename, timeIter, ext);
8192  }
8193 
8194  return filename;
8195 }
8196 
8197 string CConfig::GetFilename_Iter(const string& filename_iter, unsigned long curInnerIter, unsigned long curOuterIter) const {
8198  const auto iter = GetMultizone_Problem() ? curOuterIter : curInnerIter;
8199  std::stringstream iter_ss;
8200  iter_ss << filename_iter << "_" << std::setw(6) << std::setfill('0') << iter;
8201  return iter_ss.str();
8202 }
8203 
8204 string CConfig::GetUnsteady_FileName(string val_filename, int val_iter, string ext) const {
8205 
8206  string UnstExt="", UnstFilename = val_filename;
8207  char buffer[50];
8208 
8209  /*--- Check that a positive value iteration is requested (for now). ---*/
8210 
8211  if (val_iter < 0) {
8212  SU2_MPI::Error("Requesting a negative iteration number for the restart file!!", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
8213  }
8214 
8215  unsigned short lastindex = UnstFilename.find_last_of(".");
8216  UnstFilename = UnstFilename.substr(0, lastindex);
8217 
8218  /*--- Append iteration number for unsteady cases ---*/
8219 
8220  if (Time_Domain) {
8221 
8222  if ((val_iter >= 0) && (val_iter < 10)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0000%d", val_iter);
8223  if ((val_iter >= 10) && (val_iter < 100)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_000%d", val_iter);
8224  if ((val_iter >= 100) && (val_iter < 1000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_00%d", val_iter);
8225  if ((val_iter >= 1000) && (val_iter < 10000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0%d", val_iter);
8226  if (val_iter >= 10000) SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d", val_iter);
8227  UnstExt = string(buffer);
8228  }
8229  UnstExt += ext;
8230  UnstFilename.append(UnstExt);
8231 
8232  return UnstFilename;
8233 }

8239 
8240  unsigned short lastindex = multizone_filename.find_last_of(".");
8241  multizone_filename = multizone_filename.substr(0, lastindex);
8242 
8243  if (Multizone_Problem) {
8244  SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
8245  multizone_filename.append(string(buffer));
8246  }
8247 
8248  multizone_filename += ext;
8249  return multizone_filename;
8250 }

8292 string CConfig::GetObjFunc_Extension(string val_filename) const {
8293 
8294  string AdjExt, Filename = val_filename;
8295 
8296  if (ContinuousAdjoint || DiscreteAdjoint) {
8297 
8298  /*--- Remove filename extension (.dat) ---*/
8299 
8300  unsigned short lastindex = Filename.find_last_of(".");
8301  Filename = Filename.substr(0, lastindex);
8302 
8303  if (nObj==1) {
8304  switch (Kind_ObjFunc[0]) {
8305  case DRAG_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cd"; break;
8306  case LIFT_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cl"; break;
8307  case SIDEFORCE_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_csf"; break;
8308  case INVERSE_DESIGN_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_invpress"; break;
8309  case INVERSE_DESIGN_HEATFLUX: AdjExt = "_invheat"; break;
8310  case MOMENT_X_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cmx"; break;
8311  case MOMENT_Y_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cmy"; break;
8312  case MOMENT_Z_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cmz"; break;
8313  case EFFICIENCY: AdjExt = "_eff"; break;
8314  case EQUIVALENT_AREA: AdjExt = "_ea"; break;
8315  case NEARFIELD_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_nfp"; break;
8316  case FORCE_X_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cfx"; break;
8317  case FORCE_Y_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cfy"; break;
8318  case FORCE_Z_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cfz"; break;
8319  case THRUST_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_ct"; break;
8320  case TORQUE_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cq"; break;
8321  case TOTAL_HEATFLUX: AdjExt = "_totheat"; break;
8322  case MAXIMUM_HEATFLUX: AdjExt = "_maxheat"; break;
8323  case AVG_TEMPERATURE: AdjExt = "_avtp"; break;
8324  case FIGURE_OF_MERIT: AdjExt = "_merit"; break;
8325  case BUFFET_SENSOR: AdjExt = "_buffet"; break;
8326  case SURFACE_TOTAL_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_pt"; break;
8327  case SURFACE_STATIC_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_pe"; break;
8328  case SURFACE_STATIC_TEMPERATURE: AdjExt = "_T"; break;
8329  case SURFACE_MASSFLOW: AdjExt = "_mfr"; break;
8330  case SURFACE_UNIFORMITY: AdjExt = "_uniform"; break;
8331  case SURFACE_SECONDARY: AdjExt = "_second"; break;
8332  case SURFACE_MOM_DISTORTION: AdjExt = "_distort"; break;
8333  case SURFACE_SECOND_OVER_UNIFORM: AdjExt = "_sou"; break;
8334  case SURFACE_PRESSURE_DROP: AdjExt = "_dp"; break;
8335  case SURFACE_SPECIES_0: AdjExt = "_avgspec0"; break;
8336  case SURFACE_SPECIES_VARIANCE: AdjExt = "_specvar"; break;
8337  case SURFACE_MACH: AdjExt = "_mach"; break;
8338  case CUSTOM_OBJFUNC: AdjExt = "_custom"; break;

8349  }
8350  }
8351  else{
8352  AdjExt = "_combo";
8353  }
8354  Filename.append(AdjExt);
8355

8357  Filename.append(".dat");
8358 
8359  }

8395 
8396 void CConfig::SetGlobalParam(MAIN_SOLVER val_solver,
8397  unsigned short val_system) {
8398 
8399  /*--- Set the simulation global time ---*/
8400 
8401  Current_UnstTime = static_cast<su2double>(TimeIter)*Delta_UnstTime;
8402  Current_UnstTimeND = static_cast<su2double>(TimeIter)*Delta_UnstTimeND;
8403 
8404  /*--- Set the solver methods ---*/
8405 
8406  auto SetFlowParam = [&]() {
8407  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
8408  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
8409  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
8410  MUSCL_Flow, NONE);
8411  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
8412  }
8413  };
8414 
8415  auto SetTurbParam = [&]() {
8416  if (val_system == RUNTIME_TURB_SYS) {
8417  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Turb, Kind_Centered_Turb,
8418  Kind_Upwind_Turb, Kind_SlopeLimit_Turb,
8419  MUSCL_Turb, NONE);
8420  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Turb);
8421  }
8422  };
8423 
8424  auto SetSpeciesParam = [&]() {
8425  if (val_system == RUNTIME_SPECIES_SYS) {
8426  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Species, Kind_Centered_Species,
8427  Kind_Upwind_Species, Kind_SlopeLimit_Species,
8428  MUSCL_Species, NONE);
8429  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Species);
8430  }
8431  };
8432 
8433  auto SetAdjFlowParam = [&]() {
8434  if (val_system == RUNTIME_ADJFLOW_SYS) {
8435  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjFlow, Kind_Centered_AdjFlow,
8436  Kind_Upwind_AdjFlow, Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjFlow,
8437  MUSCL_AdjFlow, NONE);
8438  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_AdjFlow);
8439  }
8440  };
8441 
8442  switch (val_solver) {
8443  case MAIN_SOLVER::EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_EULER:
8444  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_EULER:
8445  SetFlowParam();
8446  break;
8447  case MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_NAVIER_STOKES:
8448  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_NAVIER_STOKES:
8449  SetFlowParam();
8450  SetSpeciesParam();
8451 
8452  if (val_system == RUNTIME_HEAT_SYS) {
8453  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Heat, CENTERED::NONE, UPWIND::NONE, LIMITER::NONE, NONE, NONE);
8454  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Heat);
8455  }
8456  break;
8457  case MAIN_SOLVER::RANS: case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS:
8458  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_RANS: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_RANS:
8459  SetFlowParam();
8460  SetTurbParam();
8461  SetSpeciesParam();
8462 
8463  if (val_system == RUNTIME_TRANS_SYS) {
8464  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Turb, Kind_Centered_Turb,
8465  Kind_Upwind_Turb, Kind_SlopeLimit_Turb,
8466  MUSCL_Turb, NONE);
8467  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Turb);
8468  }
8469  if (val_system == RUNTIME_HEAT_SYS) {
8470  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Heat, CENTERED::NONE, UPWIND::NONE, LIMITER::NONE, NONE, NONE);
8471  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Heat);
8472  }
8473  break;
8474  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_EULER:
8475  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_NAVIER_STOKES:
8476  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_RANS:
8477  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_LES:
8478  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_EULER:
8479  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_NS:
8480  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_RANS:
8481  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
8482  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_FEM_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
8483  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
8484  MUSCL_Flow, Kind_FEM_Flow);
8485  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_FEM_Flow);
8486  }
8487  break;
8488  case MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_EULER:
8489  case MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES:
8490  SetFlowParam();
8491  SetAdjFlowParam();
8492  break;
8493  case MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_RANS:
8494  SetFlowParam();
8495  SetTurbParam();
8496  SetAdjFlowParam();
8497 
8498  if (val_system == RUNTIME_ADJTURB_SYS) {
8499  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjTurb, Kind_Centered_AdjTurb,
8500  Kind_Upwind_AdjTurb, Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjTurb,
8501  MUSCL_AdjTurb, NONE);
8502  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_AdjTurb);
8503  }
8504  break;
8505  case MAIN_SOLVER::HEAT_EQUATION:
8506  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_HEAT:
8507  if (val_system == RUNTIME_HEAT_SYS) {
8508  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(NONE, CENTERED::NONE, UPWIND::NONE, LIMITER::NONE, NONE, NONE);
8509  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Heat);
8510  }
8511  break;
8512 
8513  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_ELASTICITY:
8514  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM:
8515 
8516  Current_DynTime = static_cast<su2double>(TimeIter)*Delta_DynTime;
8517 
8518  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FEA_SYS) {
8519  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(NONE, CENTERED::NONE, UPWIND::NONE, LIMITER::NONE , NONE, NONE);
8520  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(NONE);
8521  }
8522  break;
8523

8550 unsigned short CConfig::GetMarker_Periodic_Donor(string val_marker) const {
8551  unsigned short iMarker_PerBound, jMarker_PerBound, kMarker_All;
8552 
8553  /*--- Find the marker for this periodic boundary. ---*/
8554  for (iMarker_PerBound = 0; iMarker_PerBound < nMarker_PerBound; iMarker_PerBound++)
8555  if (Marker_PerBound[iMarker_PerBound] == val_marker) break;
8556 
8557  /*--- Find corresponding donor. ---*/
8558  for (jMarker_PerBound = 0; jMarker_PerBound < nMarker_PerBound; jMarker_PerBound++)
8559  if (Marker_PerBound[jMarker_PerBound] == Marker_PerDonor[iMarker_PerBound]) break;
8560 
8561  /*--- Find and return global marker index for donor boundary. ---*/
8562  for (kMarker_All = 0; kMarker_All < nMarker_CfgFile; kMarker_All++)
8563  if (Marker_PerBound[jMarker_PerBound] == Marker_All_TagBound[kMarker_All]) break;
8564 
8565  return kMarker_All;
8566 }

8733 bool CConfig::GetVolumetric_Movement() const {
8734  bool volumetric_movement = false;
8735 
8736  if (GetSurface_Movement(AEROELASTIC) ||
8737  GetSurface_Movement(AEROELASTIC_RIGID_MOTION)||
8738  GetSurface_Movement(EXTERNAL) ||
8739  GetSurface_Movement(EXTERNAL_ROTATION)){
8740  volumetric_movement = true;
8741  }
8742 
8743  if (Kind_SU2 == SU2_COMPONENT::SU2_DEF ||
8744  Kind_SU2 == SU2_COMPONENT::SU2_DOT ||
8745  DirectDiff)
8746  { volumetric_movement = true;}
8747 
8748  return volumetric_movement;
8749 }

9209 pair<WALL_TYPE, su2double> CConfig::GetWallRoughnessProperties(string val_marker) const {
9210  unsigned short iMarker = 0;
9211  short flag = -1;
9212  pair<WALL_TYPE, su2double> WallProp;
9213 
9214  if (nMarker_HeatFlux > 0 || nMarker_Isothermal > 0 || nMarker_HeatTransfer || nMarker_CHTInterface > 0) {
9215  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_HeatFlux; iMarker++)
9216  if (Marker_HeatFlux[iMarker] == val_marker) {
9217  flag = iMarker;
9218  WallProp = make_pair(Kind_Wall[flag], Roughness_Height[flag]);
9219  return WallProp;
9220  }
9221  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_Isothermal; iMarker++)
9222  if (Marker_Isothermal[iMarker] == val_marker) {
9223  flag = nMarker_HeatFlux + iMarker;
9224  WallProp = make_pair(Kind_Wall[flag], Roughness_Height[flag]);
9225  return WallProp;
9226  }
9227  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_HeatTransfer; iMarker++)
9228  if (Marker_HeatTransfer[iMarker] == val_marker) {
9229  flag = nMarker_HeatFlux + nMarker_Isothermal + iMarker;
9230  WallProp = make_pair(Kind_Wall[flag], Roughness_Height[flag]);
9231  return WallProp;
9232  }
9233  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_CHTInterface; iMarker++)
9234  if (Marker_CHTInterface[iMarker] == val_marker) {
9235  flag = nMarker_HeatFlux + nMarker_Isothermal + nMarker_HeatTransfer + iMarker;
9236  WallProp = make_pair(Kind_Wall[flag], Roughness_Height[flag]);
9237  return WallProp;
9238  }
9239  }
9240 
9241  WallProp = make_pair(WALL_TYPE::SMOOTH, 0.0);
9242  return WallProp;
9243 }
9244

9633 short CConfig::FindInterfaceMarker(unsigned short iInterface) const {
9634 
9635  /*--- The names of the two markers that form the interface. ---*/
9636  const auto& sideA = Marker_ZoneInterface[2*iInterface];
9637  const auto& sideB = Marker_ZoneInterface[2*iInterface+1];
9638 
9639  for (unsigned short iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_All; iMarker++) {
9640  /*--- If the marker is sideA or sideB of the interface (order does not matter). ---*/
9641  const auto& tag = Marker_All_TagBound[iMarker];
9642  if ((tag == sideA) || (tag == sideB)) return iMarker;
9643  }
9644  return -1;
9645 }

9654 
9655 void CConfig::Tock(double val_start_time, string val_function_name, int val_group_id) {
9656 
9657 #ifdef PROFILE
9658 
9659  double val_stop_time = 0.0, val_elapsed_time = 0.0;
9660 
9661  val_stop_time = SU2_MPI::Wtime();
9662 
9663  /*--- Compute the elapsed time for this subroutine ---*/
9664  val_elapsed_time = val_stop_time - val_start_time;
9665 
9666  /*--- Store the subroutine name and the elapsed time ---*/
9667  Profile_Function_tp.push_back(val_function_name);
9668  Profile_Time_tp.push_back(val_elapsed_time);
9669  Profile_ID_tp.push_back(val_group_id);
9670 
9671 #endif
9672 
9673 }
9674 
9675 void CConfig::SetProfilingCSV(void) {
9676 
9677 #ifdef PROFILE
9678 
9679  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
9680  int size = SINGLE_NODE;
9681 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
9682  SU2_MPI::Comm_rank(SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &rank);
9683  SU2_MPI::Comm_size(SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &size);
9684 #endif
9685 
9686  /*--- Each rank has the same stack trace, so the they have the same
9687  function calls and ordering in the vectors. We're going to reduce
9688  the timings from each rank and extract the avg, min, and max timings. ---*/
9689 
9690  /*--- First, create a local mapping, so that we can extract the
9691  min and max values for each function. ---*/
9692 
9693  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < Profile_Function_tp.size(); i++) {
9694 
9695  /*--- Add the function and initialize if not already stored (the ID
9696  only needs to be stored the first time).---*/
9697  if (Profile_Map_tp.find(Profile_Function_tp[i]) == Profile_Map_tp.end()) {
9698 
9699  vector<int> profile; profile.push_back(i);
9700  Profile_Map_tp.insert(pair<string,vector<int> >(Profile_Function_tp[i],profile));
9701 
9702  } else {
9703 
9704  /*--- This function has already been added, so simply increment the
9705  number of calls and total time for this function. ---*/
9706 
9707  Profile_Map_tp[Profile_Function_tp[i]].push_back(i);
9708 
9709  }
9710  }
9711 
9712  /*--- We now have everything gathered by function name, so we can loop over
9713  each function and store the min/max times. ---*/
9714 
9715  int map_size = 0;
9716  for (map<string,vector<int> >::iterator it=Profile_Map_tp.begin(); it!=Profile_Map_tp.end(); ++it) {
9717  map_size++;
9718  }
9719 
9720  /*--- Allocate and initialize memory ---*/
9721 
9722  double *l_min_red = NULL, *l_max_red = NULL, *l_tot_red = NULL, *l_avg_red = NULL;
9723  int *n_calls_red = NULL;
9724  double* l_min = new double[map_size];
9725  double* l_max = new double[map_size];
9726  double* l_tot = new double[map_size];
9727  double* l_avg = new double[map_size];
9728  int* n_calls = new int[map_size];
9729  for (int i = 0; i < map_size; i++)
9730  {
9731  l_min[i] = 1e10;
9732  l_max[i] = 0.0;
9733  l_tot[i] = 0.0;
9734  l_avg[i] = 0.0;
9735  n_calls[i] = 0;
9736  }
9737 
9738  /*--- Collect the info for each function from the current rank ---*/
9739 
9740  int func_counter = 0;
9741  for (map<string,vector<int> >::iterator it=Profile_Map_tp.begin(); it!=Profile_Map_tp.end(); ++it) {
9742 
9743  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < (it->second).size(); i++) {
9744  n_calls[func_counter]++;
9745  l_tot[func_counter] += Profile_Time_tp[(it->second)[i]];
9746  if (Profile_Time_tp[(it->second)[i]] < l_min[func_counter])
9747  l_min[func_counter] = Profile_Time_tp[(it->second)[i]];
9748  if (Profile_Time_tp[(it->second)[i]] > l_max[func_counter])
9749  l_max[func_counter] = Profile_Time_tp[(it->second)[i]];
9750 
9751  }
9752  l_avg[func_counter] = l_tot[func_counter]/((double)n_calls[func_counter]);
9753  func_counter++;
9754  }
9755 
9756  /*--- Now reduce the data ---*/
9757 
9758  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
9759  l_min_red = new double[map_size];
9760  l_max_red = new double[map_size];
9761  l_tot_red = new double[map_size];
9762  l_avg_red = new double[map_size];
9763  n_calls_red = new int[map_size];
9764  }
9765 
9766 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
9767  MPI_Reduce(n_calls, n_calls_red, map_size, MPI_INT, MPI_SUM, MASTER_NODE, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
9768  MPI_Reduce(l_tot, l_tot_red, map_size, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_SUM, MASTER_NODE, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
9769  MPI_Reduce(l_avg, l_avg_red, map_size, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_SUM, MASTER_NODE, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
9770  MPI_Reduce(l_min, l_min_red, map_size, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_MIN, MASTER_NODE, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
9771  MPI_Reduce(l_max, l_max_red, map_size, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_MAX, MASTER_NODE, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
9772 #else
9773  memcpy(n_calls_red, n_calls, map_size*sizeof(int));
9774  memcpy(l_tot_red, l_tot, map_size*sizeof(double));
9775  memcpy(l_avg_red, l_avg, map_size*sizeof(double));
9776  memcpy(l_min_red, l_min, map_size*sizeof(double));
9777  memcpy(l_max_red, l_max, map_size*sizeof(double));
9778 #endif
9779 
9780  /*--- The master rank will write the file ---*/
9781 
9782  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
9783 
9784  /*--- Take averages over all ranks on the master ---*/
9785 
9786  for (int i = 0; i < map_size; i++) {
9787  l_tot_red[i] = l_tot_red[i]/(double)size;
9788  l_avg_red[i] = l_avg_red[i]/(double)size;
9789  n_calls_red[i] = n_calls_red[i]/size;
9790  }
9791 
9792  /*--- Now write a CSV file with the processed results ---*/
9793 
9794  ofstream Profile_File;
9795  Profile_File.precision(15);
9796  Profile_File.open("profiling.csv");
9797 
9798  /*--- Create the CSV header ---*/
9799 
9800  Profile_File << "\"Function_Name\", \"N_Calls\", \"Avg_Total_Time\", \"Avg_Time\", \"Min_Time\", \"Max_Time\", \"Function_ID\"" << endl;
9801 
9802  /*--- Loop through the map and write the results to the file ---*/
9803 
9804  func_counter = 0;
9805  for (map<string,vector<int> >::iterator it=Profile_Map_tp.begin(); it!=Profile_Map_tp.end(); ++it) {
9806 
9807  Profile_File << scientific << it->first << ", " << n_calls_red[func_counter] << ", " << l_tot_red[func_counter] << ", " << l_avg_red[func_counter] << ", " << l_min_red[func_counter] << ", " << l_max_red[func_counter] << ", " << (int)Profile_ID_tp[(it->second)[0]] << endl;
9808  func_counter++;
9809  }
9810 
9811  Profile_File.close();
9812 
9813  }
9814 
9815  delete [] l_min;
9816  delete [] l_max;
9817  delete [] l_avg;
9818  delete [] l_tot;
9819  delete [] n_calls;
9820  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
9821  delete [] l_min_red;
9822  delete [] l_max_red;
9823  delete [] l_avg_red;
9824  delete [] l_tot_red;
9825  delete [] n_calls_red;
9826  }
9827 
9828 #endif
9829 
9830 }
9831 
9832 void CConfig::GEMM_Tick(double *val_start_time) const {
9833 
9834 #ifdef PROFILE
9835 
9836 #ifdef HAVE_MKL
9837  *val_start_time = dsecnd();
9838 #else
9839  *val_start_time = SU2_MPI::Wtime();
9840 #endif
9841 
9842 #endif
9843 
9844 }
9845 
9846 void CConfig::GEMM_Tock(double val_start_time, int M, int N, int K) const {
9847 
9848 #ifdef PROFILE
9849 
9850  /* Determine the timing value. The actual function called depends on
9851  the type of executable. */
9852  double val_stop_time = 0.0;
9853 
9854 #ifdef HAVE_MKL
9855  val_stop_time = dsecnd();
9856 #else
9857  val_stop_time = SU2_MPI::Wtime();
9858 #endif
9859 
9860  /* Compute the elapsed time. */
9861  const double val_elapsed_time = val_stop_time - val_start_time;
9862 
9863  /* Create the CLong3T from the M-N-K values and check if it is already
9864  stored in the map GEMM_Profile_MNK. */
9865  CLong3T MNK(M, N, K);
9866  map<CLong3T, int>::iterator MI = GEMM_Profile_MNK.find(MNK);
9867 
9868  if(MI == GEMM_Profile_MNK.end()) {
9869 
9870  /* Entry is not present yet. Create it. */
9871  const int ind = GEMM_Profile_MNK.size();
9872  GEMM_Profile_MNK[MNK] = ind;
9873 
9874  GEMM_Profile_NCalls.push_back(1);
9875  GEMM_Profile_TotTime.push_back(val_elapsed_time);
9876  GEMM_Profile_MinTime.push_back(val_elapsed_time);
9877  GEMM_Profile_MaxTime.push_back(val_elapsed_time);
9878  }
9879  else {
9880 
9881  /* Entry is already present. Determine its index in the
9882  map and update the corresponding vectors. */
9883  const int ind = MI->second;
9884  ++GEMM_Profile_NCalls[ind];
9885  GEMM_Profile_TotTime[ind] += val_elapsed_time;
9886  GEMM_Profile_MinTime[ind] = min(GEMM_Profile_MinTime[ind], val_elapsed_time);
9887  GEMM_Profile_MaxTime[ind] = max(GEMM_Profile_MaxTime[ind], val_elapsed_time);
9888  }
9889 
9890 #endif
9891 
9892 }
9893 
9894 void CConfig::GEMMProfilingCSV(void) {
9895 
9896 #ifdef PROFILE
9897 
9898  /* Initialize the rank to the master node. */
9899  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
9900 
9901 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
9902  /* Parallel executable. The profiling data must be sent to the master node.
9903  First determine the rank and size. */
9904  int size;
9905  SU2_MPI::Comm_rank(SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &rank);
9906  SU2_MPI::Comm_size(SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &size);
9907 
9908  /* Check for the master node. */
9909  if(rank == MASTER_NODE) {
9910 
9911  /* Master node. Loop over the other ranks to receive their data. */
9912  for(int proc=1; proc<size; ++proc) {
9913 
9914  /* Block until a message from this processor arrives. Determine
9915  the number of entries in the receive buffers. */
9916  SU2_MPI::Status status;
9917  SU2_MPI::Probe(proc, 0, SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &status);
9918 
9919  int nEntries;
9920  SU2_MPI::Get_count(&status, MPI_LONG, &nEntries);
9921 
9922  /* Allocate the memory for the receive buffers and receive the
9923  three messages using blocking receives. */
9924  vector<long> recvBufNCalls(nEntries);
9925  vector<double> recvBufTotTime(nEntries);
9926  vector<double> recvBufMinTime(nEntries);
9927  vector<double> recvBufMaxTime(nEntries);
9928  vector<long> recvBufMNK(3*nEntries);
9929 
9930  SU2_MPI::Recv(recvBufNCalls.data(), recvBufNCalls.size(),
9931  MPI_LONG, proc, 0, SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &status);
9932  SU2_MPI::Recv(recvBufTotTime.data(), recvBufTotTime.size(),
9933  MPI_DOUBLE, proc, 1, SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &status);
9934  SU2_MPI::Recv(recvBufMinTime.data(), recvBufMinTime.size(),
9935  MPI_DOUBLE, proc, 2, SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &status);
9936  SU2_MPI::Recv(recvBufMaxTime.data(), recvBufMaxTime.size(),
9937  MPI_DOUBLE, proc, 3, SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &status);
9938  SU2_MPI::Recv(recvBufMNK.data(), recvBufMNK.size(),
9939  MPI_LONG, proc, 4, SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &status);
9940 
9941  /* Loop over the number of entries. */
9942  for(int i=0; i<nEntries; ++i) {
9943 
9944  /* Create the CLong3T from the M-N-K values and check if it is already
9945  stored in the map GEMM_Profile_MNK. */
9946  CLong3T MNK(recvBufMNK[3*i], recvBufMNK[3*i+1], recvBufMNK[3*i+2]);
9947  map<CLong3T, int>::iterator MI = GEMM_Profile_MNK.find(MNK);
9948 
9949  if(MI == GEMM_Profile_MNK.end()) {
9950 
9951  /* Entry is not present yet. Create it. */
9952  const int ind = GEMM_Profile_MNK.size();
9953  GEMM_Profile_MNK[MNK] = ind;
9954 
9955  GEMM_Profile_NCalls.push_back(recvBufNCalls[i]);
9956  GEMM_Profile_TotTime.push_back(recvBufTotTime[i]);
9957  GEMM_Profile_MinTime.push_back(recvBufMinTime[i]);
9958  GEMM_Profile_MaxTime.push_back(recvBufMaxTime[i]);
9959  }
9960  else {
9961 
9962  /* Entry is already present. Determine its index in the
9963  map and update the corresponding vectors. */
9964  const int ind = MI->second;
9965  GEMM_Profile_NCalls[ind] += recvBufNCalls[i];
9966  GEMM_Profile_TotTime[ind] += recvBufTotTime[i];
9967  GEMM_Profile_MinTime[ind] = min(GEMM_Profile_MinTime[ind], recvBufMinTime[i]);
9968  GEMM_Profile_MaxTime[ind] = max(GEMM_Profile_MaxTime[ind], recvBufMaxTime[i]);
9969  }
9970  }
9971  }
9972  }
9973  else {
9974 
9975  /* Not the master node. Create the send buffer for the MNK data. */
9976  vector<long> sendBufMNK(3*GEMM_Profile_NCalls.size());
9977  for(map<CLong3T, int>::iterator MI =GEMM_Profile_MNK.begin();
9978  MI!=GEMM_Profile_MNK.end(); ++MI) {
9979 
9980  const int ind = 3*MI->second;
9981  sendBufMNK[ind] = MI->first.long0;
9982  sendBufMNK[ind+1] = MI->first.long1;
9983  sendBufMNK[ind+2] = MI->first.long2;
9984  }
9985 
9986  /* Send the data to the master node using blocking sends. */
9987  SU2_MPI::Send(GEMM_Profile_NCalls.data(), GEMM_Profile_NCalls.size(),
9988  MPI_LONG, MASTER_NODE, 0, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
9989  SU2_MPI::Send(GEMM_Profile_TotTime.data(), GEMM_Profile_TotTime.size(),
9990  MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, 1, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
9991  SU2_MPI::Send(GEMM_Profile_MinTime.data(), GEMM_Profile_MinTime.size(),
9992  MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, 2, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
9993  SU2_MPI::Send(GEMM_Profile_MaxTime.data(), GEMM_Profile_MaxTime.size(),
9994  MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, 3, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
9995  SU2_MPI::Send(sendBufMNK.data(), sendBufMNK.size(),
9996  MPI_LONG, MASTER_NODE, 4, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
9997  }
9998 
9999 #endif
10000 
10001  /*--- The master rank will write the file ---*/
10002  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
10003 
10004  /* Store the elements of the map GEMM_Profile_MNK in
10005  vectors for post processing reasons. */
10006  const unsigned int nItems = GEMM_Profile_MNK.size();
10007  vector<long> M(nItems), N(nItems), K(nItems);
10008  for(map<CLong3T, int>::iterator MI =GEMM_Profile_MNK.begin();
10009  MI!=GEMM_Profile_MNK.end(); ++MI) {
10010 
10011  const int ind = MI->second;
10012  M[ind] = MI->first.long0;
10013  N[ind] = MI->first.long1;
10014  K[ind] = MI->first.long2;
10015  }
10016 
10017  /* In order to create a nicer output the profiling data is sorted in
10018  terms of CPU time spent. Create a vector of pairs for carrying
10019  out this sort. */
10020  vector<pair<double, unsigned int> > sortedTime;
10021 
10022  for(unsigned int i=0; i<GEMM_Profile_TotTime.size(); ++i)
10023  sortedTime.push_back(make_pair(GEMM_Profile_TotTime[i], i));
10024 
10025  sort(sortedTime.begin(), sortedTime.end());
10026 
10027  /* Open the profiling file. */
10028  ofstream Profile_File;
10029  Profile_File.precision(15);
10030  Profile_File.open("gemm_profiling.csv");
10031 
10032  /* Create the CSV header */
10033  Profile_File << "\"Total_Time\", \"N_Calls\", \"Avg_Time\", \"Min_Time\", \"Max_Time\", \"M\", \"N\", \"K\", \"Avg GFLOPs\"" << endl;
10034 
10035  /* Loop through the different items, where the item with the largest total time is
10036  written first. As sortedTime is sorted in increasing order, the sequence of
10037  sortedTime must be reversed. */
10038  for(vector<pair<double, unsigned int> >::reverse_iterator rit =sortedTime.rbegin();
10039  rit!=sortedTime.rend(); ++rit) {
10040  /* Determine the original index in the profiling vectors. */
10041  const unsigned int ind = rit->second;
10042  const double AvgTime = GEMM_Profile_TotTime[ind]/GEMM_Profile_NCalls[ind];
10043  const double GFlops = 2.0e-9*M[ind]*N[ind]*K[ind]/AvgTime;
10044 
10045  /* Write the data. */
10046  Profile_File << scientific << GEMM_Profile_TotTime[ind] << ", " << GEMM_Profile_NCalls[ind] << ", "
10047  << AvgTime << ", " << GEMM_Profile_MinTime[ind] << ", " << GEMM_Profile_MaxTime[ind] << ", "
10048  << M[ind] << ", " << N[ind] << ", " << K[ind] << ", " << GFlops << endl;
10049  }
10050 
10051  /* Close the file. */
10052  Profile_File.close();
10053  }
10054 
10055 #endif
10056 
10057 }

10067 void CConfig::SetMultizone(const CConfig *driver_config, const CConfig* const* config_container){
10068 
10069  for (unsigned short iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++){
10070 
10071  if (config_container[iZone]->GetTime_Domain() != GetTime_Domain()){
10072  SU2_MPI::Error("Option TIME_DOMAIN must be the same in all zones.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10073  }
10074  if (config_container[iZone]->GetnTime_Iter() != GetnTime_Iter()){
10075  SU2_MPI::Error("Option TIME_ITER must be the same in all zones.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10076  }
10077  if (config_container[iZone]->GetnOuter_Iter() != GetnOuter_Iter()){
10078  SU2_MPI::Error("Option OUTER_ITER must be the same in all zones.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10079  }
10080  if (config_container[iZone]->GetTime_Step() != GetTime_Step()){
10081  SU2_MPI::Error("Option TIME_STEP must be the same in all zones.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10082  }
10083  if (config_container[iZone]->GetUnst_CFL() != 0.0){
10084  SU2_MPI::Error("Option UNST_CFL_NUMBER cannot be used in multizone problems (must be 0),"
10085  " use a fixed TIME_STEP instead.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10086  }
10087  if (config_container[iZone]->GetMultizone_Problem() != GetMultizone_Problem()){
10088  SU2_MPI::Error("Option MULTIZONE must be the same in all zones.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10089  }
10090  if (config_container[iZone]->GetMultizone_Mesh() != GetMultizone_Mesh()){
10091  SU2_MPI::Error("Option MULTIZONE_MESH must be the same in all zones.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10092  }
10093  if(config_container[iZone]->GetWnd_Cauchy_Crit() == true){
10094  SU2_MPI::Error("Option WINDOW_CAUCHY_CRIT must be deactivated for multizone problems.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10095  }
10096  }
10097  if(driver_config->GetWnd_Cauchy_Crit() == true){
10098  SU2_MPI::Error("Option WINDOW_CAUCHY_CRIT must be deactivated for multizone problems.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10099  }
10100 
10101  bool multiblockDriver = false;
10102  for (unsigned short iFiles = 0; iFiles < driver_config->GetnVolumeOutputFiles(); iFiles++){
10103  if (driver_config->GetVolumeOutputFiles()[iFiles] == OUTPUT_TYPE::PARAVIEW_MULTIBLOCK){
10104  multiblockDriver = true;
10105  }
10106  }
10107 
10108  bool multiblockZone = false;
10109  for (unsigned short iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++){
10110  multiblockZone = false;
10111  for (unsigned short iFiles = 0; iFiles < config_container[iZone]->GetnVolumeOutputFiles(); iFiles++){
10112  if (config_container[iZone]->GetVolumeOutputFiles()[iFiles] == OUTPUT_TYPE::PARAVIEW_MULTIBLOCK){
10113  multiblockZone = true;
10114  }
10115  }
10116  if (multiblockZone != multiblockDriver){
10117  SU2_MPI::Error("To enable PARAVIEW_MULTIBLOCK output, add it to OUTPUT_FILES option in main config and\n"
10118  "remove option from sub-config files.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10119  }
10120  }
10121 
10122  /*--- Fix the Time Step for all subdomains, for the case of time-dependent problems ---*/
10123  if (driver_config->GetTime_Domain()){
10124  Delta_UnstTime = driver_config->GetTime_Step();
10125  Delta_DynTime = driver_config->GetTime_Step();
10126 
10127  Time_Domain = true;
10128  }
10129 
10130  /*------------------------------------------------------------*/
10131  /*------ Determine the special properties of the problem -----*/
10132  /*------------------------------------------------------------*/
10133 
10134  bool fluid_zone = false;
10135  bool structural_zone = false;
10136 
10137  /*--- If there is at least a fluid and a structural zone ---*/
10138  for (auto iZone = 0u; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
10139  fluid_zone |= config_container[iZone]->GetFluidProblem();
10140  structural_zone |= config_container[iZone]->GetStructuralProblem();
10141  }
10142 
10143  if (structural_zone) Relaxation = true;
10144 
10145  /*--- If the problem has FSI properties ---*/
10146  FSI_Problem = fluid_zone && structural_zone;
10147 
10148  Multizone_Residual = true;
10149 }
